yle=\"color:#f56d22;\">NCAA Tournament</span>]]\n{{CBB schedule entry\n | date         = Mar. 16\n | time         = 12:15 PM\n | w/l          = w\n | nonconf      = yes\n | away         = \n | neutral      = yes\n | rank         = (4S)\n | opponent     = [[2006\u201307 Albany Great Danes men's basketball team|Albany]]\n | opprank      = (13S)\n | site_stadium = [[Nationwide Arena]]\n | site_cityst  = [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus, OH]]\n | gamename     = NCAA Tournament First Round\n | tv           = [[NCAA March Madness (CBS/Turner)|CBS/CSTV]]\n | score        = 84\u201357\n | overtime     = \n | attend       = &nbsp;\n | record       = 21\u201310\n | conference   = \n}}\n{{CBB schedule entry\n | date         = Mar. 18\n | time         = 12:10 PM\n | w/l          = l\n | nonconf      = yes\n | away         = \n | neutral      = yes\n | rank         = (4S)\n | opponent     = [[2006\u201307 Tennessee Volunteers basketball team|Tennessee]]\n | opprank      = (5S)\n | site_stadium = Nationwide Arena\n | site_cityst  = Columbus, OH\n | gamename     = NCAA Tournament Second Round\n | tv           = CBS\n | score        = 77\u201374\n | overtime     = \n | attend       = &nbsp;\n | record       = 21\u201311\n | conference   = \n}}\n{{CBB schedule end\n|poll=[[AP Poll]]\n|timezone=[[Eastern Time Zone|Eastern Time]]\n}}\n<ref name=\"UVaSchedule\">{{cite web\n| title = 2006\u20132007 Schedule\n| url = http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-baskbl/sched/va-m-baskbl-sched.html\n| website = VIRGINIASPORTS.COM - The University of Virginia Official Athletic Site\n| accessdate = December 11, 2014\n}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Virginia Cavaliers men's basketball navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2006-07 Virginia Cavaliers men's basketball team}}\n[[Category:Virginia Cavaliers men's basketball seasons]]\n[[Category:2006\u201307 Atlantic Coast Conference men's basketball season|Virginia]]\n[[Category:2007 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament participants|Virginia]]\n[[Category:2006 in sports in Virginia]]\n[[Category:2007 in sports in Virginia]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links to2007 ACC Tournament(link changed to2007 ACC Men's Basketball Tournament) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2006%E2%80%9307_Virginia_Cavaliers_men%27s_basketball_team"}
{"title_page": "Wayne Garfield", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Wayne Garfield\n| image       = \n| image_size  =\n| caption     =\n| birth_date  = \n| birth_place = \n| residence   = \n| nationality = United States\n| education   = \n| occupation  = songwriter, vocalist, producer\n| spouse      = \n| partner     =\n| children    = \n| parents     =\n| relatives   =\n| signature   =\n| website     = \n| footnotes   =\n}}\n\n'''Wayne Garfield''' is a composer, collaborating songwriter, vocalist, social entrepreneur, community activists, and producer for four decades. He is a contributor, and co founder of the vaunted music collective [[Change (band)]], contributing to musical pop culture. Chance launched the career of [[Luther Vandross]] with the hit song \"[[The Glow of Love]]\". Which became #1 on the [[Billboard]] Dance/Disco Chart in the summer of 1980.<ref>http://www.spiritmusicgroup.com/Clients/Library/Wayne-Garfield</ref><ref>https://www.writersrulecoalition.org/about_us</ref>\n\n==Career==\nGarfield's career started as a singer with the [[The Voices of East Harlem]] a rock and soul group. The group was formed in 1969 in Harlem, New York City.  The group recorded with [[Elektra Records|Elektra]], Just Sunshine, and [[Motown]]. The Voices of East Harlem was a 20-member ensemble aged 12 to 21. The group worked with producers [[Leroy Hutson]] and [[Curtis Mayfield]]. \nGarfield was a member of the [[Change (band)]] collected. He has composed music for [[Janet Jackson]], [[Luther Vandross]], [[Roy Ayers]], [[Kurtis Blow]], [[Taj Mahal]], soundtrack for the movie Coffy, Salt-N-Pepa, [[Aretha Franklin]], [[Theo Croker]], and [[Fela Kuti]]. He has functioned in the capacity of composer, lyricist, manager and arranger for three decades. In 1973 Garfield wrote the soundtrack for the movie [[Coffy]]. The movie was directed by [[Jack Hill]].<ref>https://secondhandsongs.com/artist/19425</ref><ref>https://tidal.com/browse/artist/6739475</ref>\n\nHe has worked with [[Angela Winbush]] and Debye Burrell to develop their careers.\n\nIn 1986 Garfield united [[Kurtis Blow]] and [[Bob Dylan]] in producing \"Street Rock\", which became a hip-hop crossover.\n\nIn 2002,  Garfield formed the advocacy group \u201cWriters Rule Coalition\u201d, for songwriters to gain award recognition.\n\nIn 2003, the National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences Board of Trustees awarded the Winners Certificate to songwriters and producers of Grammy nominated and winning recordings containing samples. Which gave writers and producers recognition for their contribution.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Composer===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* 2019\tEverything and More: The Complete Collection 1980\u20132019; (Change Collective) \t\n* 2018\tKOD; J. Cole\t\n* 2016\tEscape Velocity; Theo Croker\t\n* 2014\tThe Box Set Series; Luther Vandross\t\n* 2013\t12\" Disco: The Collection\t\t\n* 2011\tLove & Revolution; Nicola Conte\t\n* 2010\tBest of Number Ones; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2010\tIcon: Number Ones; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2009\tLouder;\tBig Ali\tRecording\n* 2009\tNumber Ones; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2009\tOld School Jams, Vol. 8\t\t\n* 2009\tThe Best; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2008\tDrew's Famous Just Dance & Party; The Hit Crew\t\n* 2008\tFrom A Distant Point Of View 2nd Edition; Geb.El\t\n* 2008\tSunset Chill: Ibiza Edition\t\t\n* 2006\tForever, for Always, for Luther, Vol. 2\t\t\n* 2006\tIn the House of Love; Dimitri from Paris\t\n* 2005\tCafe Ibiza, Vol. 6: The Ambient & Chill Out Album\t\t\n* 2005\tComplete 80's Soul Weekender\t\t\n* 2005\tNova Latino, Vol. 2\t\t\n* 2005\tRock On: Breakout Years\tLuther Vandross\t\n* 2004\tArtist Collection: Luther Vandross; Luther Vandross\t\n* 2004\tFrom Janet. To Damita Jo: The Videos [Amaray]; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2004\tFrom Janet. To Damita Jo: The Videos [Jewelcase]; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2004\tIn the House; Dimitri from Paris\t\n* 2004\tSmooth Sax Tribute to Janet Jackson\t\t\n* 2004\tThe String Quartet