ows]]\"\n*[[Count Five]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Psychotic Reaction]]\n* [[The 13th Floor Elevators]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[You're Gonna Miss Me (song)|You're Gonna Miss Me]]\"\n*The 13th Floor Elevators&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Psychedelic Sounds of the 13th Floor Elevators|Roller Coaster]]\"\n* [[The Music Machine]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Talk Talk (The Music Machine song)|Talk Talk]]\"\n* [[The Troggs]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Wild Thing (The Troggs song)|Wild Thing]]\"\n* [[The Yardbirds]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Shapes of Things]]\"\n\nNote: The 13th Floor Elevators coined the term \"psychedelic rock\" in 1966, the first band ever referred to as psychedelic rock.\n\n==1967==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]]{{refn|group=note|name=B\u00d6C|The band was originally named \"Soft White Underbelly\", and went through multiple band names before settling on their current name in 1971.}}\n* [[Budgie (band)|Budgie]]\n* [[Creedence Clearwater Revival]]\n* [[Elf (band)|Elf]]\n* [[Genesis (band)|Genesis]]\n* [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]]\n*[[T. Rex (band)|T. Rex]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Cream (band)|Cream]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Disraeli Gears]]'' US #4 UK #5\n* [[Jefferson Airplane]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Surrealistic Pillow]]'' US #3\n* [[The Jimi Hendrix Experience]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Are You Experienced]]'' US #5 UK #2\n* The Jimi Hendrix Experience&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Axis Bold As Love]]'' US #3 UK #5\n* [[The Rolling Stones]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Their Satanic Majesties Request]]'' US #2 UK #3\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Vanilla Fudge (album)|Vanilla Fudge]]'' US #6\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[The Doors]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The End (The Doors song)|The End]]\"\n* The Doors&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Light My Fire]]\"\n* The Doors&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Break on Through (To the Other Side)]]\"\n* [[Jefferson Airplane]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Somebody to Love (Jefferson Airplane song)|Somebody to Love]]\"\n* Jefferson Airplane&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[White Rabbit (Jefferson Airplane song)|White Rabbit]]\"\n* [[Jimi Hendrix]]&nbsp;\u2013