 \"[[Born To Be Wild]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* [[Blue Cheer]]'s guitarist [[Leigh Stephens]] leaves the band after the release of the ''[[Outsideinside]]'' album. He is replaced by [[Randy Holden]].\n* [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]]'s bass guitarist [[Rushton Moreve]] is fired from the band. He will be eventually replaced by [[Nick St. Nicholas]].\n\n==1969==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[April Wine]]\n* [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]]\n* [[Focus (band)|Focus]]\n* [[Gary Moore]]\n* [[Grand Funk Railroad]]\n* [[Hawkwind]]\n* [[Humble Pie (band)|Humble Pie]]\n* [[Judas Priest]]\n* [[Mountain (band)|Mountain]]\n* [[Slade]]\n* [[Steeleye Span]]\n* [[Thin Lizzy]]\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]]\n* [[Uriah Heep (band)|Uriah Heep]]\n* [[Wishbone Ash]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[The Jeff Beck Group]]\n* [[The Jimi Hendrix Experience]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Pretties for You]]''\n* [[Blue Cheer]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[New! Improved!]]''\n* [[Blue Cheer]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Blue Cheer (album)|Blue Cheer]]''\n* [[Coven (band)|Coven]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Witchcraft Destroys Minds & Reaps Souls]]''\n* [[Cream (band)|Cream]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Goodbye (Cream album)|Goodbye]]'' US #2 UK #1\n* [[Creedence Clearwater Revival]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Green River (album)|Green River]]''\n* Creedence Clearwater Revival&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bayou Country (album)|Bayou Country]]''\n* Creedence Clearwater Revival&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Willy and the Poor Boys]]''\n* [[Deep Purple]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Deep Purple (album)|Deep Purple]]''\n* [[Grand Funk Railroad]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[On Time]]'' US #27\n* Grand Funk Railroad&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Grand Funk (album)|Grand Funk]]'' US #11\n* [[High Tide (band)|High Tide]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Sea Shanties (High Tide album)|Sea Shanties]]''\n* [[Humble Pie (band)|Humble Pie]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[As Safe as Yesterday Is]]''\n* Humble Pie&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Town and Country (album)|Town and Country]]''\n* [[Leslie West]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Mountain (Leslie West album)|Mountain]]''\n* [[Iron Butterfly]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Ball (Iron Butterfly album)|Ball]]'' US #3\n* [[King Crimson]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[In the Court of the Crimson King]]'' UK #5\n* [[Led Zeppelin]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Led Zeppelin (album)|Led Zeppelin]]'' US #10 UK #6\n* Led Zeppelin&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Led Zeppelin II]]'' US #1 UK #1\n* MC5 \u2013 [[Kick Out The Jams]] US #30\n* [[Neil Young]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Everybody Knows This Is Nowhere]]''\n* [[Slade]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Beginnings (Ambrose Slade album)|Beginnings]]''\n* [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[At Your Birthday Party]]'' US #7\n* Steppenwolf&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Monster (Steppenwolf album)|Monster]]'' US #17\n* [[The Stooges]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Stooges (album)|The Stooges]]''\n* [[The Jeff Beck Group]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Beck-Ola]]'' US #15\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Near the Beginning]]''\n* Vanilla Fudge&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Rock & Roll (Vanilla Fudge album)|Rock & Roll]]''\n* [[The Who]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Tommy (The Who album)|Tommy]]'' US #4\n* [[Yes (band)|Yes]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Yes (Yes album)|Yes]]''\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[The Beatles]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[I Want You (She's So Heavy)]]\"<ref>\"Reading the Beatles: Cultural Studies, Literary Criticism, and the Fab Four\" \"the 1969 track \"I Want You (She's So Heavy)\", where heavy metal inscribes an earthy sexuality to Yoko Ono\"</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=All Together Now|first=David|last=Rowley|quote=...the heavy metal of 'I Want You (She's so Heavy)'...}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |first=Nicholas|last=Schaffner |title=The Beatles Forever |url=https://archive.org/details/beatlesforever00scha|url-access=registration|year=1978 |page=[https://archive.org/details/beatlesforever00scha/page/125 125] |quote='I Want You (She's So Heavy)' \u2014 the weightiest slab of 'heavy metal' the Beatles ever quarried.}}</ref>\n* [[Creedence Clearwater Revival]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Bad Moon Rising (song)|Bad Moon Rising]]\"\n* Creedence Clearwater Revival&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Lodi (Creedence Clearwater Revival song)|Lodi]]\"\n* Creedence Clearwater Revival&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Born on the Bayou]]\"\n* Creedence Clearwater Revival&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Proud Mary]]\"\n* Creedence Clearwater Revival&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Fortunate Son]]\"\n* [[King Crimson]]&nbsp;- \"[[21st Century Schizoid Man]]\"\n* [[Led Zeppelin]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Communication Breakdown]]\"\n* Led Zeppelin&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Dazed and Confused (song)#Led Zeppelin studio recording|Dazed and Confused]]\"\n* Led Zeppelin&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Good Times Bad Times]]\"\n* Led Zeppelin&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Ramble On]]\"\n* Led Zeppelin&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Whole Lotta Love]]\" US #4 AUS #1\n* [[Pink Floyd]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Nile Song]]\"\n* The Stooges \u2013 \"[[I Wanna Be Your Dog]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* The hard rock group [[The Who]] releases the concept album ''[[Tommy (rock opera)|Tommy]]'', about a deaf, dumb and blind boy who wins a mass following after becoming a pinball guru. The album's consistent themes, plot, story and interlinking songs set the template for many other hard-rock artists to attempt such concept albums.\n* [[Deep Purple]]'s lead singer [[Rod Evans]] is fired after the recording of ''[[Deep Purple (album)|Deep Purple]]'' and is replaced by [[Ian Gillan]]. The band's bass guitarist [[Nick Simper]] is replaced next by [[Roger Glover]] on the demand of Ian Gillan.\n* Guitarist [[Randy Holden]] leaves [[Blue Cheer]] after recording 3 titles of the ''[[New! Improved!]]'' album. He is replaced by Bruce Stephens.\n* Due to disagreements with [[John Kay (musician)|John Kay]], lead guitarist [[Michael Monarch]] leaves [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]] after the release of the ''[[At Your Birthday Party]]'' album. He will be replaced later on by [[Larry Byrom]].\n* Four weeks after being fired from the band for drug and alcohol abuse, [[The Rolling Stones|Rolling Stones]] founder [[Brian Jones]] is found dead in his swimming pool, aged 27, on 3 July.\n* [[Woodstock]] was held in August 15\u201318\n\n==1970==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Aerosmith]]\n* [[Bloodrock]]\n* [[Cactus (American band)|Cactus]]\n* [[ELO]]\n* [[Queen (band)|Queen]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[The Jimi Hendrix Experience]]\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]] (1st Hiatus)\n* [[The Beatles]]\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[The Jeff Beck Group]]\n* [[The Jimi Hendrix Experience]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Easy Action]]''\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Sabbath (album)|Black Sabbath]]'' UK #8\n* Black Sabbath&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Paranoid (album)|Paranoid]]'' UK #1\n* [[Black Widow (band)|Black Widow]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Sacrifice (Black Widow album)|Sacrifice]]''\n* [[Bloodrock]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bloodrock (album)]]''\n* [[Bloodrock]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bloodrock 2]]''\n* [[Blue Cheer]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Original Human Being]]''\n* [[Cactus (American band)|Cactus]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Cactus (Cactus album)|Cactus]]''\n* [[Deep Purple]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Deep Purple in Rock]]'' UK #4\n* [[Grand Funk Railroad]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Closer to Home]]''\n* [[Humble Pie (band)|Humble Pie]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Humble Pie (album)|Humble Pie]]''\n* [[Iron Butterfly]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Metamorphosis (Iron Butterfly album)|Metamorphosis]]''\n* [[Josefus]]&nbsp;\u2013''Dead Man''\n* [[King Crimson]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[In the Wake of Poseidon]]''\n* King Crimson&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Lizard]]''\n* [[Led Zeppelin]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Led Zeppelin III]]'' US #1 UK #1\n*[[May Blitz]]&nbsp;\u2013''[[May Blitz (album)|May Blitz]]''\n* [[Mountain (band)|Mountain]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Climbing!]]''\n* [[November (band)|November]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[En ny tid \u00e4r h\u00e4r...]]''\n* [[Sir Lord Baltimore]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Kingdom Come (Sir Lord Baltimore album)|Kingdom Come]]''\n* [[Slade]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Play it Loud]]''\n* [[Status Quo (band)|Status Quo]]&nbsp;-''[[Dog Of Two Head]]''\n* [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Steppenwolf 7|7]]''\n* [[The Stooges]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Fun House (The Stooges album)|Fun House]]''\n* [[