orpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Fly to the Rainbow]]'', first album with guitarist [[Uli Jon Roth|Ulrich Roth]]\n* [[Slade]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Old New Borrowed and Blue]]''\n* Slade&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Slade in Flame (album)|Slade in Flame]]''\n* [[Status Quo (band)|Status Quo]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Quo (Status Quo album)|Quo]]''\n* [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Slow Flux]]''\n* [[Thin Lizzy]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Nightlife (Thin Lizzy album)|Nightlife]]''\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Phenomenon (UFO album)|Phenomenon]]'', their first with ex-Scorpions guitarist [[Michael Schenker]]\n* [[Uriah Heep (band)|Uriah Heep]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Wonderworld (album)|Wonderworld]]''\n* [[Wishbone Ash]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[There's the Rub]]''\n* [[Yes (band)|Yes]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Relayer]]''\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[Aerosmith]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Same Old Song and Dance]]\"\n* [[Deep Purple]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Burn (Deep Purple song)|Burn]]\"\n* Deep Purple&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Mistreated (song)|Mistreated]]\"\n* Deep Purple&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Soldier of Fortune (Deep Purple song)|Soldier of Fortune]]\"\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Cold Gin]]\"\n* Kiss&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Deuce (song)|Deuce]]\"\n* Kiss&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Goin' Blind]]\"\n* Kiss&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Hotter than Hell (Kiss song)|Hotter Than Hell]]\"\n* Kiss&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Let Me Go, Rock 'n' Roll]]\"\n* Kiss&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Strutter]]\"\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Working Man]]\"\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Doctor Doctor (UFO song)|Doctor Doctor]]\"\n* UFO&nbsp;\u2013 \"Rock Bottom\"\n\n===Events===\n* The drummer [[John Rutsey]] of [[Rush (band)|Rush]] quits and [[Neil Peart]] joins as a permanent member.\n* [[Sammy Hagar]] leaves Montrose to go solo.\n\n==1975==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Iron Maiden]]\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]\n* [[Quiet Riot]]\n* [[Rainbow (English band)|Rainbow]]\n* [[The Runaways]]\n* [[Riot (band)|Riot]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Bloodrock]]\n* [[Blue Cheer]]