atio]], [[Exciter (band)|Exciter]], [[Marty Friedman (musician)|Marty Friedman]] (with Vixen/[[Hawaii (band)|Hawaii]]), [[Enuff Z'nuff|Derek Frigo]], [[Keel (band)|Keel]], [[Manilla Road]], [[Shawn Lane]], [[The Rods]], [[Vicious Rumors]], [[Virgin Steele]], [[Wild Dogs]], and [[Lyle Workman]].\n* [[Monsters of Rock|Monsters of Rock Festival]] features [[AC/DC]] with support from [[Whitesnake]], [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]], [[Slade]], [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]] and [[More (British band)|More]].\n* ''[[Kerrang!]]'' magazine launches its first issue June 1981.\n\n==1982==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Armored Saint]]\n* [[Death Angel]]\n* [[Dio (band)|Dio]]\n* [[Flotsam and Jetsam (band)|Flotsam and Jetsam]]\n* [[Kreator]]\n* [[Possessed (band)|Possessed]]\n* [[Queensr\u00ffche]]\n* [[Tankard (band)]]\n* Vixen/[[Hawaii (band)|Hawaii]]\n* [[Warlock (band)|Warlock]]\n* [[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]]\n* [[X Japan]]\n* [[Tarot (band)|Tarot]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Praying Mantis (band)|Praying Mantis]]\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]]\n\n===Albums===\nUK Chart Info courtesy of the book ''[[Guinness Hits of the 80s]]''\n* [[Aerosmith]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Rock in a Hard Place]]''\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Restless and Wild]]''\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Zipper Catches Skin]]''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;- ''[[Metal on Metal]]''\n* [[April Wine]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Power Play (April Wine album)|Power Play]]''\n* [[Bad Company]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Rough Diamonds (album)|Rough Diamonds]]'' UK #15\n* [[Bernie Torme]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Turn Out the Lights (album)|Turn Out the Lights]]'' UK #50\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]]&nbsp;- ''Asian Volcano''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]]&nbsp;- ''Warning from Stardust''\n* [[Budgie (band)|Budgie]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Deliver Us from Evil (Budgie album)|Deliver Us from Evil]]'' UK #62\n* [[Cheap Trick]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[One on One (Cheap Trick album)|One On One]]'' UK #95\n* [[Diamond Head (English band)|Diam