 Live]]'' UK #39\n* [[Michael Schenker Group]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[One Night at Budokan]]'' UK #5\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Speak of the Devil (Ozzy Osbourne album)|Talk of the Devil]]'' UK #21\n* [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Eagle Has Landed (album)|The Eagle Has Landed]]'' UK #5\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[Asia (band)|Asia]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Heat of the Moment (Asia song)|Heat Of The Moment]]\" UK #46\n* [[Asia (band)|Asia]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Only Time Will Tell (song)|Only Time Will Tell]]\" UK #54\n* [[Cheap Trick]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[If You Want My Love]]\" UK #57\n* [[Diamond Head (English band)|Diamond Head]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Borrowed Time (Diamond Head album)|In The Heat Of The Night]]\" UK #67\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Number of the Beast (song)|The Number of the Beast]]\" UK #18\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Run to the Hills]]\" UK #7\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Hallowed Be Thy Name]]\"\n* [[Journey (band)|Journey]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Don't Stop Believin']]\" UK #62\n* [[Journey (band)|Journey]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Who's Crying Now]]\" UK #46\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[You've Got Another Thing Comin']]\" UK #66\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Electric Eye]]\"\n* [[Michael Schenker Group]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Dancer (Michael Schenker Group song)|Dancer]]\" UK #52\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Iron Fist (song)|Iron Fist]]\" UK #29\n* [[Rainbow (rock band)|Rainbow]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Straight Between the Eyes|Stone Cold]]\" UK #34\n* [[Rainbow (rock band)|Rainbow]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Street of Dreams (Rainbow song)|Street of Dreams]]\" UK #52\n* [[Robert Plant]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Burning Down One Side]]\" UK #73\n* [[Robert Plant]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Big Log]]\" UK #11\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[New World Man]]\" UK #42\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Subdivisions (song)|Subdivisions]]\" UK #53\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Countdown (Rush song)|Countdown]]\" UK #36\n* [[Sammy Hagar]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Piece Of My Heart]]\" UK #67\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[No One Like You]]\" UK #65\n* [[Spider (British band)|Spider]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Why D'Ya Lie to Me]]\" UK #65\n* [[Status Quo (band)|Status Quo]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Dear John (Status Quo song)|Dear John]]\" UK #10\n* [[Status Quo (band)|Status Quo]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[She Don't Fool Me]]\" UK #36\n* [[Survivor (band)|Survivor]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Eye of the Tiger]]\" UK #1\n* [[Tygers of Pan Tang]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Rendezvous\" UK #49\n* [[Tygers of Pan Tang]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Paris by Air\" UK #63\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Let It Rain\" UK #62\n* [[Whitesnake]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Here I Go Again]]\" UK #34\n\n===Events===\n* [[Iron Maiden]]'s first album with Bruce Dickinson, ''[[The Number of the Beast (album)|The Number of the Beast]]'', becomes the first [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] album to reach No.1 in the U.K. music charts.\n* Drummer [[Clive Burr]] is fired from Iron Maiden and replaced by [[Nicko McBrain]].\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]'s guitarist \"Fast\" Eddie Clarke leaves the band and is replaced by ex-[[Thin Lizzy]] guitarist [[Brian Robertson (guitarist)|Brian Robertson]].\n* [[Judas Priest]]'s single \"[[You've Got Another Thing Comin']]\" becomes the first [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] single to break into the Billboard U.S. Top 20 Singles.\n* [[Ace Frehley]] leaves [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] and is replaced by [[Vinnie Vincent]]. Last tour in make-up\n* [[Megaforce Records]] founded.\n* [[Metal Blade Records]] formed by [[Brian Slagel]] and released through it first compilation album [[Metal Massacre]]. It is famous for \"shedding light\" on bands such as [[Metallica]], [[Ratt]], [[Armored Saint]], and many more.\n* Ozzy Osbourne's guitarist Randy Rhoads dies in an aeroplane accident on March 19.\n* [[Ronnie James Dio]] leaves Black Sabbath, and is replaced by former Deep Purple vocalist [[Ian Gillan]]. Dio forms [[Dio (band)|Dio]] with Black Sabbath drummer [[Vinny Appice]], former Rainbow and [[Wild Horses (British band)|Wild Horses]] bassist [[Jimmy Bain]], and [[Sweet Savage (Irish band)|Sweet Savage]] guitarist [[Vivian Campbell]].\n* Snowy White leaves Thin Lizzy, and is replaced by [[John Sykes]].\n* Ozzy Osbourne and [[Sharon Osbourne]] get married and become the first Solo Heavy Metal Singer and Manager to get married.\n* [[Klaus Meine]] recorded ''Blackout'' album for Scorpions after recovering from a serious throat surgery.\n* Monsters of Rock Festival features as headliner [[Status Quo (band)|Status Quo]] with support from [[Gillan (band)|Gillan]], [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]], [[Hawkwind]], [[Uriah Heep (band)|Uriah Heep]] and [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]].\n\n==1983==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Alcatrazz]]\n* [[Bathory (band)|Bathory]]\n* [[Bon Jovi]]\n* [[Cinderella (band)|Cinderella]]\n* [[The Cult]]\n* [[Death (metal band)|Death]]\n* [[D'erlanger]]\n* [[Fastway (band)|Fastway]]\n* [[Fates Warning]]\n* [[L.A. Guns]]\n* [[Lita Ford]]\n* [[Megadeth]]\n* [[Melvins]]\n* [[Metal Church]]\n* [[Poison (American band)|Poison]]\n* [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]]\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]\n* [[Waysted]]\n* [[White Lion]]\n* [[Raging Slab]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Riot (band)|Riot]]\n* [[The Who]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[AC/DC]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Flick of the Switch]]'' UK #4 AUS #3\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Balls to the Wall]]''\n* [[Alcatrazz]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[No Parole from Rock 'n' Roll]]''\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[DaDa]]''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Forged in Fire]]''\n* [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Siogo]]'' US #82\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Born Again (Black Sabbath album)|Born Again]]'' UK #4\n* [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Revolution by Night]]''\n* [[Def Leppard]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Pyromania (album)|Pyromania]]'' US #2\n* [[Diamond Head (English band)|Diamond Head]]&nbsp;- ''[[Canterbury (album)|Canterbury]]''\n* [[Dio (band)|Dio]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Holy Diver]]''\n* [[Europe (band)|Europe]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Europe (Europe album)|Europe]]''\n* [[Exciter (band)|Exciter]]&nbsp;- ''[[Heavy Metal Maniac]]''\n* [[Fastway (band)|Fastway]]&nbsp;- ''[[Fastway (album)|Fastway]]''\n* [[Gary Moore]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Victims of the Future]]''\n* [[Girlschool]]&nbsp;- ''[[Play Dirty (album)|Play Dirty]]''\n* [[Grand Funk Railroad]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[What's Funk?]]''\n* [[Hanoi Rocks]]&nbsp;- ''[[Back to Mystery City]]''\n* [[Heart (band)|Heart]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Passionworks]]''\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Piece of Mind]]'' UK #3\n* [[King's X]]&nbsp;- ''[[Sneak Preview (album)|Sneak Preview]]''\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Lick It Up]]'' UK #7\n* [[Krokus (band)|Krokus]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Headhunter (album)|Headhunter]]''\n* [[Loudness (band)|Loudness]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Law of Devil's Land]]''\n* [[Magnum (band)|Magnum]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Eleventh Hour (Magnum album)|The Eleventh Hour]]''\n* [[Manilla Road]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Crystal Logic]]''\n* [[Manowar]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Into Glory Ride]]''\n* [[Meat Loaf]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Midnight at the Lost and Found]]''\n* [[Metallica]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Kill 'Em All]]''\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Melissa (Mercyful Fate album)|Melissa]]''\n* [[Michael Schenker Group]]&nbsp;- ''[[Built to Destroy]]''\n* [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Shout at the Devil]]''\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Another Perfect Day]]''\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bark at the Moon]]''\n* [[Pantera]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Metal Magic]]''\n* [[Picture (band)|Picture]]&nbsp;- ''Eternal Dark''\n* [[Queensr\u00ffche]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Queensr\u00ffche (EP)|Queensr\u00ffche]]'' (EP)\n* [[Quiet Riot]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Metal Health]]'' US #1\n* [[Rainbow (English band)|Rainbow]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bent out of Shape]]''\n* [[Ratt]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Ratt (EP)|Ratt]]'' (EP)\n* [[Riot (band)|Riot]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Born in America]]''\n* [[Satan (band)|Satan]]&nbsp;- ''Court in t