ns\"\n* Iron Maiden&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Trooper]]\"\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Freewheel Burning]]\"\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Lick It Up (song)|Lick It Up]]\"\n* [[Metallica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Mechanix|The Four Horsemen]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Jump in the Fire]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Seek & Destroy]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Whiplash (Metallica song)|Whiplash]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Hit The Lights]]\"\n* [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Looks That Kill]]\"\n* M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Shout at the Devil (song)|Shout at the Devil]]\"\n* M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Too Young to Fall in Love]]\"\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Bark at the Moon (song)|Bark at the Moon]]\"\n* [[Quiet Riot]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Cum on Feel the Noize#Quiet Riot cover version|Cum on Feel the Noize]]\"\n* Quiet Riot&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Metal Health (song)|Metal Health (Bang Your Head)]]\"\n* [[Slayer]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Black Magic\"\n* Slayer&nbsp;\u2013 \"Metal Storm/Face the Slayer\"\n* [[Suicidal Tendencies]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"I Saw Your Mommy\"\n* Suicidal Tendencies&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Institutionalized (song)|Institutionalized]]\"\n* Accept- \"Balls to the Wall\"\n\n===Events===\n* At the end of the year, drummer Phil \"Philthy Animal\" Taylor and guitarist [[Brian Robertson (guitarist)|Brian Robertson]] leave [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]. The band is reborn with a new, four-piece line-up ([[Lemmy Kilmister|Kilmister]]/[[Phil Campbell (musician)|Campbell]]/[[W\u00fcrzel|Burston]]/Gill).\n* Dave Mustaine, lead guitar player for Metallica, is fired for drug/alcohol abuse, and is replaced by Exodus guitarist Kirk Hammett\n* Yngwie Malmsteen debuts with [[Steeler (American band)|Steeler]], then leaves to form Alcatrazz with [[Graham Bonnet]], and finally goes solo and is replaced in Alcatrazz by [[Steve Vai]].\n* \"Heavy Metal Day\" at the 1983 [[US Festival]] features headliner [[Van Halen]], with support from [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]], [[Triumph (band)|Triumph]], [[Judas Priest]], [[Ozzy Osbourne]], [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]] and [[Quiet Riot]] sets a United States single-day concert attendance record.\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] publicly remove their makeup on [[MTV]] and experience a slight resurgence in their career\n* [[Quiet Riot]]'s ''[[Metal Health]]'' becomes the first [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] album to reach No.1 in the [[Billboard magazine|Billboard United States music charts]] and is followed by albums by [[Twisted Sister]], and [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]]\n* [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Shout at the Devil]]'' Becomes a huge hit marking one of the turning points into commercialisation of Heavy Metal. Often called \"The Breakthrough Metal album\".\n* [[Monsters Of Rock Festival]] features Headliner [[Whitesnake]] with support from [[Meat Loaf]], [[ZZ Top]], [[Twisted Sister]], [[Dio (band)|Dio]] and [[Diamond Head (English band)|Diamond Head]].\n* [[Metal Forces mag]] launches its first issue Autumn 1983\n\n==1984==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Annihilator (band)|Annihilator]]\n* [[Atheist (band)|Atheist]]\n* [[Blind Guardian]]\n* [[Celtic Frost]]\n* [[Gwar]]\n* [[Helloween]]\n* [[King Kobra]]\n* [[Mayhem (band)|Mayhem]]\n* [[Morbid Angel]]\n* [[Nuclear Assault]]\n* [[Obituary (band)|Obituary]]\n* [[Sadus]]\n* [[Sepultura]]\n* [[Soundgarden]]\n* [[Steve Vai]] (solo)\n* [[Stratovarius]]\n* [[The Quireboys]]\n* [[Warfaze]]\n* [[Warrant (American band)|Warrant]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Rainbow (English band)|Rainbow]]\n* [[Thin Lizzy]]\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]] (Second hiatus)\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Fistful of Metal]]''\n* [[April Wine]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Animal Grace]]''\n* [[Armored Saint]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[March of the Saint]]''\n* [[Bathory (band)|Bathory]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bathory (album)|Bathory]]''\n* [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Vertical Smiles]]''\n* [[Black 'n Blue]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black 'n Blue (album)|Black 'n Blue]]'' US #129\n* [[Blue Cheer]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Beast Is Back]]''\n* [[Bon Jovi]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bon Jovi (album)|Bon Jovi]]''\n* [[Cirith Ungol (band)|Cirith Ungol]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[King of the Dead (album)|King of the Dead]]''\n* [[The Cult]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dreamtime (The Cult album)|Dreamtime]]''\n* [[Deep Purple]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Perfect Strangers (album)|Perfect Strangers]]'' UK #5\n* [[Dio (band)|Dio]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Last in Line]]'' UK #4\n* [[Dokken]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Tooth and Nail (Dokken album)|Tooth and Nail]]''\n* [[Europe (band)|Europe]]&nbsp;- ''[[Wings of Tomorrow]]''\n* [[Exciter (band)|Exciter]]&nbsp;- ''[[Violence & Force]]''\n* [[Fastway (band)|Fastway]]&nbsp;- ''[[All Fired Up (Fastway album)|All Fired Up]]''\n* [[Fates Warning]]&nbsp;- ''[[Night on Br\u00f6cken]]''\n* [[Foreigner (band)|Foreigner]]&nbsp;- ''[[Agent Provocateur (album)|Agent Provocateur]]''\n* [[Hanoi Rocks]]&nbsp;- ''[[Two Steps from the Move]]''\n* [[Icon (band)|Icon]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Icon (Icon album)|Icon]]''\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Powerslave]]'' UK #2\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Defenders of the Faith]]''\n* [[King Crimson]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Three of a Perfect Pair]]''\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Animalize]]''\n* [[Loudness (band)|Loudness]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Disillusion (album)|Disillusion]]''\n* [[Yngwie J. Malmsteen]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Rising Force]]''\n* [[Manowar (band)|Manowar]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Hail to England]]''\n* Manowar&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Sign of the Hammer]]''\n* [[Meat Loaf]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bad Attitude (album)|Bad Attitude]]''\n* [[Metallica]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Ride the Lightning]]''\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Don't Break the Oath]]''\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[No Remorse (Mot\u00f6rhead album)|No Remorse]]''\n* [[Pantera]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Projects in the Jungle]]''\n* [[Picture (band)|Picture]]&nbsp;- ''Traitor''\n* [[Praying Mantis (band)|Praying Mantis]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Thr