u2013 \"[[Stranger in a Strange Land (Iron Maiden song)|Stranger in a Strange Land]]\"\n* Iron Maiden&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Wasted Years]]\"\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Locked In (song)|Locked In]]\"\n* Judas Priest&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Turbo Lover (song)|Turbo Lover]]\"\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Peace Sells]]\"\n* Megadeth&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Wake Up Dead]]\"\n* Megadeth&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Good Mourning/Black Friday]]\"\n* [[Metal Church]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Start the Fire\"\n* Metal Church&nbsp;\u2013 \"Watch the Children Pray\"\n* [[Metallica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Master of Puppets]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Battery (song)|Battery]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Welcome Home (Sanitarium)]]\"\n* Metallica&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Disposable Heroes]]\"\n* [[Slayer]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Angel of Death (Slayer song)|Angel of Death]]\"\n* Slayer&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Raining Blood]]\"\n* [[Tarot (band)|Tarot]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Wings of Darkness]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* [[KNAC]] airs on radio airplay in Los Angeles, California for the first time.\n* Former [[Thin Lizzy]] bassist and lead singer [[Phil Lynott]] dies at the age of 36 on 4 January from pneumonia and heart failure due to septicaemia, after a long period of drink and drug abuse.\n* [[Metallica]]'s bassist [[Cliff Burton]] dies at the age of 24 on September 27 in a bus accident in Sweden. [[Jason Newsted]] from [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]] band [[Flotsam and Jetsam (band)|Flotsam and Jetsam]] is hired after auditions are held.\n* The success of [[Bon Jovi]]'s ''[[Slippery When Wet]]'' ushers in the era of [[glam metal]]. The album went on to sell 28 million copies worldwide, and is one of the best-selling albums of all time.\n* [[Monsters Of Rock Festival]] features Headliner [[Ozzy Osbourne]] with support from [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]], [[Def Leppard]], [[Mot\u00f6rhead]], [[Bad News (band)|Bad News]] and [[Warlock (band)|Warlock]].\n* [[Metal Hammer mag]] launches its first issue for the UK market, October 1986\n\n==1987==\n===N