'[[Cross Purposes Live]]''\n* [[Heart (band)|Heart]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Road Home (Heart album)|The Road Home]]''\n* [[Mayhem (band)|Mayhem]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dawn of the Black Hearts]]''\n* [[Overkill (band)|Overkill]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Wrecking Your Neck]]''\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live Bites]]''\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live at the Fillmore (Testament album)|Live at the Fillmore]]''\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Fueled\"\n* [[Dream Theater]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Silent Man\"\n* [[Gamma Ray (band)|Gamma Ray]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Land Of The Free\"\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Man on the Edge]]\" UK #10\n* [[Kreator]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Isolation\"\n* Kreator&nbsp;\u2013 \"Lost\"\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[\u00c0 Tout le Monde|A Tout le Monde]]\"\n* [[Savatage]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Chance\"\n* Savatage&nbsp;\u2013 \"Dead Winter Dead\"\n* Savatage&nbsp;\u2013 \"Doesn't Matter Anyway\"\n* [[Skid Row (American band)|Skid Row]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Breakin' Down]]\"\n* Skid Row&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Into Another]]\"\n* Skid Row&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[My Enemy (Skid Row song)|My Enemy]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* [[Richey Edwards]], rhythm guitarist and primary songwriter of [[Manic Street Preachers]], is reported missing on February 1 after departing his hotel in London as him and bandmate [[James Dean Bradfield]] were set to fly out on a promotional tour in the [[United States]]. Edwards' car was subsequently found near the [[Severn Bridge]], a popular suicide spot between [[England]] and [[Wales]] however, his body has never been found.\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]'s guitarist Michael \"[[W\u00fcrzel]]\" Burston leaves the band.\n* MTV abruptly canceled the music television program [[Headbangers Ball|Headbanger's Ball]] in January 1995.\n* After a series of private tragedies, drummer [[Ingo Schwichtenberg]] felt unable to cope with life and committed suicide, to honor his memory, guitarist [[Roland Grapow]] bought his [[Drum kit]].\n* Los Angeles-based heavy metal radio station [[KNAC]] goes off the air and is replaced by [[KBUE]].\n\n==1996==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[3 Doors Down]]\n* [[Arch Enemy]]\n* [[Control Denied]]\n* [[Danko Jones]]\n* [[Decapitated (band)|Decapitated]]\n* [[God Forbid]]\n* [[Gojira (band)|Gojira]]\n* [[Letzte Instanz]]\n* [[Linkin Park]]\n* [[Lordi]]\n* [[Mudvayne]]\n* [[Nightwish]]\n* [[Norther]]\n* [[Pain (musical project)|Pain]]\n* [[Queens of the Stone Age]]\n* [[Saurom]]\n* [[Segression]]\n* [[Shadows Fall]]\n* [[SHOCKLET]]\n* [[Skillet (band)|Skillet]]\n* [[Slapshock]]\n* [[Spineshank]]\n* [[Tristania (band)|Tristania]]\n* [[Within Temptation]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Down (band)|Down]]\n* [[Skid Row (American band)|Skid Row]]\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[Judas Priest]](Back from hiatus with new singer [[Tim \"Ripper\" Owens]])\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] (back in full makeup and costume with [[Ace Frehley]] and [[Peter Criss]])\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Predator (album)|Predator]]''\n* [[Alice in Chains]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Unplugged (Alice in Chains)|Unplugged]]'' US #6\n* [[Holy_Land_(album)|Angra - Holy Land]]\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Plugged in Permanent]]''\n* [[Apocalyptica]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Plays Metallica by Four Cellos]]''\n* [[Arch Enemy (band)|Arch Enemy]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Earth (Arch Enemy album)|Black Earth]]''\n* [[Axel Rudi Pell]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Moon Pyramid]]''\n* [[Bathory (band)|Bathory]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Blood on Ice]]''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]]&nbsp;- ''Led by the Sun''\n* [[Bruce Dickinson]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Skunkworks (album)|Skunkworks]]''\n* [[Bush (British band)|Bush]]&nbsp;- ''[[Razorblade Suitcase]]'' US #1 CAN #1 UK #4\n* [[Cannibal Corpse]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Vile (album)|Vile]]''\n* [[Cryptopsy]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[None So Vile]]''\n* [[Darkthrone]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Total Death]]''\n* [[Deep Purple]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Purpendicular]]''\n* [[Def Leppard]]