)|Anthrax]], [[Megadeth]], [[Metallica]], and [[Slayer]]\n* [[Dio (band)|Dio]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dio at Donington UK: Live 1983 & 1987]]'' both shows were recorded in their respective years\n* [[Down (band)|Down]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Diary of a Mad Band: Europe in the Year of VI]]''\n* [[DragonForce]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Twilight Dementia]]''\n* [[Halestorm]]&nbsp;- ''[[Live in Philly 2010]]''\n* [[Halford (band)|Halford]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Live in Anaheim (Original Soundtrack)'' Originally recorded in 2003\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Rust in Peace Live]]''\n* [[Meshuggah]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Alive (Meshuggah video)|Alive]]''\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[British Steel&nbsp;\u2013 30th Anniversary&nbsp;\u2013 Live]]''\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[Avenged Sevenfold]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Nightmare (Avenged Sevenfold song)|Nightmare]]\"\n* Avenged Sevenfold&nbsp;\u2013 \"Save Me\"\n* Avenged Sevenfold&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[So Far Away (Avenged Sevenfold song)|So Far Away]]\"\n* [[Deftones]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Diamond Eyes (song)|Diamond Eyes]]\"\n* Deftones&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Rocket Skates]]\"\n* Deftones&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Diamond Eyes|Sextape]]\"\n* Deftones&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[You've Seen the Butcher]]\"\n* [[Exodus (American band)|Exodus]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Downfall\"\n* Exodus&nbsp;\u2013 \"Hammer and Life\"\n* [[Godsmack]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Crying Like a Bitch]]\"\n* [[Iron Maiden]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Coming Home\"\n* Iron Maiden&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[El Dorado (Iron Maiden song)|El Dorado]]\"\n* Iron Maiden&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Satellite 15... The Final Frontier]]\"\n* Iron Maiden&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Talisman\"\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Dialectic Chaos]]/[[This Day We Fight!]]\"\n* Megadeth&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Right to Go Insane]]\"\n* Megadeth&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Sudden Death (song)|Sudden Death]]\"\n* [[Periphery (band)|Periphery]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Icarus Lives\"\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Caravan (Rush song)|Caravan]]\"\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Lorelei\"\n* Scorpions&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Best Is Yet to Come\"\n* Scorpions&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Good Die Young\"\n* Scorpions&nbsp;\u2013 \"SLY\"\n* [[Slayer]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"World Painted Blood\"\n* [[Tarja Turunen]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Until My Last Breath\"\n\n===Events===\n* Soundgarden reunites on New Year's Day.\n* Bassist and lead singer of Type O Negative, [[Peter Steele]] age 48 dies of heart failure on April 14, 2010.\n* [[Ronnie James Dio]] dies of stomach cancer at the age of 67 on May 16, 2010.\n* On June 16, \"The Big Four of Thrash Metal\", Anthrax, Megadeth, Slayer and Metallica, play together for the first time at the Sonisphere Festival at Bemowo Airport in Warsaw, Poland.\n* Judas Priest wins the 2010 Grammy Award for Best Metal Performance of \"Dissident Aggressor.\"\n* [[Iron Maiden]]'s [[The Final Frontier]] reaches No. 1 in the [[U.K.]] for the first time since 1992's [[Fear of the Dark (Iron Maiden album)|Fear of the Dark]]. This album also marked [[Iron Maiden]]'s highest ever chart position in the United States, debuting at No. 4. Overall the release peaked at No. 1 in 28 countries.<ref name=\"FF 28 quote\">{{cite web | url = http://legacy.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=148709 | title = Iron Maiden Around The World In 66 Days | accessdate = 2011-11-20 | publisher = [[Blabbermouth.net]] }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=Jennica |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* Original Megadeth bassist Dave Ellefson rejoins the band after departing in 2002.\n* After 25 years, Mike Portnoy leaves [[Dream Theater]] on September 8, 2010.\n* Scorpions announce that they will retire after touring in support of final album Sting in the Tail.\n* AC/DC headline Download festival, marking their return to Donington for the first time in 19 years, since 1991's Monsters of Rock. Also Rage Against the Machine and Aerosmith to headline.\n* [[Paul Gray (American musician)|Paul Gray]] of [[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]] dies on May 24, 2010 of an accidental overdose of [[morphine]] and [[fentanyl]].\n* [[Michael Kiske]] formed the rock band Unisonic and began touring again after 17 years.\n\n==2011==\n\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Adrenaline Mob]]\n* [[Hacktivist (band)|Hacktivist]]\n* [[Killer Be Killed]]\n* [[Luca Turilli's Rhapsody]]\n* [[Thrown into Exile]]\n* [[Twilight Force]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Anal Cunt]] (Due to [[Seth Putnam]]'s death)\n* [[Atreyu (band)|Atreyu]] (until 2014)\n* [[Disturbed (band)|Disturbed]] (until 2015)\n* [[Fury (Australian band)|Fury]]\n* [[Luca Turilli (band)|Luca Turilli]] (solo band after split from [[Rhapsody of Fire]] and formation of [[Luca Turilli's Rhapsody]])\n* [[Mercyful Fate]] (On Hiatus)\n* [[Metalium]]\n* [[Nevermore]] (On Hiatus until [[Warrel Dane]]'s death in 2017)\n* [[Rage Against the Machine]] (On Hiatus)\n* [[Silverchair]] (On Hiatus)\n* [[Iron Butterfly]] (after the death of Original Member [[Lee Dorman]].)\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[Black Sabbath]]\n* [[Byzantine (band)|Byzantine]]\n* [[Coal Chamber]]\n* [[Ministry (band)|Ministry]]\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]\n* [[System of a Down]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Welcome 2 My Nightmare]]'' UK #7\n* [[Amaranthe]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Amaranthe (album)|Amaranthe]]''\n* [[Amon Amarth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Surtur Rising]]''\n* [[Amorphis]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Beginning of Times]]''\n* [[Anaal Nathrakh]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Passion (Anaal Nathrakh album)|Passion]]''\n* [[Animals as Leaders]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Weightless (Animals as Leaders album)|Weightless]]''\n* [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Worship Music (album)|Worship Music]]'' US #12\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Juggernaut of Justice]]''\n* [[Arch Enemy (band)|Arch Enemy]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Khaos Legions]]''\n* [[Asking Alexandria]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Reckless & Relentless]]'' US #9\n* [[Battlecross]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Pursuit of Honor''\n* [[Black Label Society]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Song Remains Not the Same]]''\n* [[Black Veil Brides]]&nbsp;\u2013 