s Whose Sinews Gave It Motion\"\n* Meshuggah&nbsp;\u2013 \"Demiurge\"\n* Meshuggah&nbsp;\u2013 \"Do Not Look Down\"\n* Meshuggah&nbsp;\u2013 \"I am Colossus\"\n* [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Sex (M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce song)|Sex]]\"\n* [[Periphery (band)|Periphery]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Make Total Destroy\"\n* Periphery&nbsp;\u2013 \"Scarlet\"\n* [[Sabaton (band)|Sabaton]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"A Lifetime of War\"\n* Sabaton&nbsp;\u2013 \"Carolus Rex\"\n* [[Sonata Arctica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"I Have a Right\"\n* Sonata Arctica&nbsp;\u2013 \"Shitload of Money\"\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Native Blood\"\n* Testament&nbsp;\u2013 \"True American Hate\"\n\n===Events===\n* Following the firing of [[Geoff Tate]] from [[Queensr\u00ffche]], Tate formed a band consisting of musicians from his solo career and titled it \"Queensr\u00ffche\", despite Queensr\u00ffche already existing with [[Todd La Torre]] as the singer. Tate believed he still owned the legal rights to the name \"Queensr\u00ffche\", and following a preliminary court hearing, both band's are temporarily allowed to use the name \"Queensr\u00ffche\" until the next court hearing in November 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/geoff-tate-wins-court-ruling-continue-using-queensryche-name/ |title=GEOFF TATE WINS COURT RULING TO CONTINUE USING QUEENSRYCHE NAME|publisher=Loudwire.com|accessdate=2014-05-19}}</ref> Both versions of Queensr\u00ffche have since released new albums and are touring under the same name as of April 2013.\n* [[Tony Iommi]] Lead Guitarist of the band [[Black Sabbath]] was diagnosed with the early stages of [[Lymphoma]] on January 9.\n* Drummer [[Dan Zimmermann]] of [[Gamma Ray (band)|Gamma Ray]] leaves the band after fifteen year stable lineup. New drummer Michael Ehr\u00e9.\n* [[Ian Watkins (Lostprophets)|Ian Watkins]], lead vocalist of [[Lostprophets]], was arrested and charged with child sex offences in December.\n* A [[Black Veil Brides]] song called \"Unbroken\" appeared on the soundtrack to the movie ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' on May 1, and is the only track released by [[Black Veil Brides]] solely on a compilation album.\n\n==2013==\n\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Band-Maid]]\n* [[DVSR]]\n* [[Lindemann (band)|Lindemann]]\n* [[Badflower]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Lostprophets]]\n* [[Static X]]\n* [[Power Quest]] (until 2016)\n\n===Albums===\n* [[After the Burial]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Wolves Within]]''\n* [[Airbourne (band)|Airbourne]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Dog Barking]]''\n* [[Alice in Chains]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Devil Put Dinosaurs Here]]'' US #2\n* [[All Hell Breaks Loose (Black Star Riders album)|All Hell Breaks Loose]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Star Riders]]''\n* [[Amaranthe]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Nexus (album)|The Nexus]]''\n* [[Amon Amarth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Deceiver of the Gods]]''\n* [[Amorphis]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Circle (Amorphis album)|Circle]]''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Hope in Hell]]''\n* [[Ashes of Ares]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Ashes of Ares (album)|Ashes of Ares]]''\n* [[Asking Alexandria]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[From Death to Destiny]]'' US #5\n* [[August Burns Red]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Rescue & Restore]]'' US #9\n* [[Avantasia]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Mystery of Time]]'' GER #2\n* [[Avenged Sevenfold]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Hail to the King (Avenged Sevenfold album)|Hail to the King]]'' US #1 UK #1\n* [[Battle Beast (band)|Battle Beast]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Battle Beast (album)|Battle Beast]]''\n* [[Battlecross]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[War of Will]]''\n* [[The Black Dahlia Murder (band)|The Black Dahlia Murder]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Everblack (The Black Dahlia Murder album)|Everblack]]''\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[13 (Black Sabbath album)|13]]'' US #1 UK #1\n* [[Black Veil Brides]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Wretched and Divine: The Story of the Wild Ones]]'' US #7\n* [[Blitzkrieg (heavy metal band)|Blitzkrieg]]&nbsp;- ''Back from Hell''\n* [[Bring Me the Horizon]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Sempiternal (album)|Sempiternal]]'' UK #3 AUS #1\n