 What We Are\"\n* [[Stratovarius]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Until the End of Days\"\n* [[Suicidal Tendencies]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Clap Like Ozzy\"\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Brotherhood of the Snake\"\n* [[Thunderstone (band)|Thunderstone]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Path\"\n\n===Events===\n* From January to September, [[Black Sabbath]] embarked on their final tour, dubbed [[The End Tour]].\n* On February 13, [[Horns Up (radio)|Horns Up]], hosted on [[KLOS]] by Stew Herrera (former DJ of [[KNAC]]), is aired for the first time. The show runs on Saturday nights on KLOS from 9PM to 12AM.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.955klos.com/horns-up-with-stew/ |title=Horns Up with Stew |publisher=[[KLOS|klos.com]] |accessdate=27 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215082211/http://www.955klos.com/horns-up-with-stew/ |archivedate=February 15, 2016 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.955klos.com/2016/03/09/horns-up-playlist-21316-w-sean-mcnabb-taime-downe/ |title=Horns Up! Playlist 2/13/16 w/ Sean McNabb & Taime Downe |publisher=[[KLOS|klos.com]] |date=13 February 2016 |accessdate=27 June 2016}}</ref>\n* In February, Brian Johnson of AC/DC was forced to leave the band or face total hearing loss.\n* In April, [[Guns N' Roses]] reunited with original guitarist [[Slash (musician)|Slash]] and bassist [[Duff McKagan]] for their [[Not in This Lifetime... Tour]].\n* On April 16, guitarist [[Angus Young]] of [[AC/DC]] joined [[Guns N' Roses]] on stage at Coachella to announce [[Axl Rose]] as AC/DC's new lead singer for the remainder of the [[Rock or Bust World Tour]] and beyond.\n* On May 7, marked the debut of [[Axl Rose]] as [[AC/DC]]'s new lead singer.\n* On September 19, bassist [[Cliff Williams]] of [[AC/DC]] released a video formally announcing his retirement from the music industry. Angus later clarified the band will continue with a new bassist and [[Axl Rose]] remaining as lead singer.\n\n==2017==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Bad Wolves]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalsucks.net/2017/11/03/bad-wolves-ex-devildriver-god-forbid-divine-heresy-sign-record-deal-release-new-single/|title=Bad Wolves (ex-DevilDriver, God Forbid, Divine Heresy) Sign Record Deal, Release New Single \u2013 MetalSucks|date=November 3, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riffrelevant.com/2017/04/18/tommy-vext-westfield-massacre-ex-divine-heresy-share-video-teaser/|title=Tommy Vext (Westfield Massacre, Ex-Divine Heresy) & Doc Coyle (God Forbid, Vagus Nerve) Unite In BAD WOLVES; Share Video Teaser|date=April 18, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/bad-wolves-feat-former-devildriver-god-forbid-divine-heresy-members-lyric-video-for-toast-to-the-ghost-song/|title=BAD WOLVES Feat. Former DEVILDRIVER, GOD FORBID, DIVINE HERESY Members: Lyric Video For 'Toast To The Ghost' Song|date=November 3, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Powerflo]]\n* [[Exit Eden]]\n* Fireburn<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/av/new-music/nails-ex-bad-brains-danzig-members-form-hardcore-band-fireburn|title=NAILS, Ex-BAD BRAINS & DANZIG Members Form Hardcore Band FIREBURN|date=August 9, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theprp.com/2017/08/08/news/fireburn-nails-ex-bad-brainsdanzig-etc-stream-debut-ep-dont-stop-youth/|title=Fireburn (Nails, Ex-Bad Brains/Danzig, Etc.) Stream Debut EP \"Don't Stop The Youth\" - Theprp.com|date=August 8, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n* The Fever<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bringthenoise.com/blog/jason-butlers-new-supergroup-the-fever-have-just|title=Jason Butler\u2019s New Supergroup The Fever Have Just Dropped A Massive New Single \"We\u2019re Coming In\" / the NOISE|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upsetmagazine.com/news/fever-jason-aalon-butlers-new-band-btw-dropped-debut-single-coming/|title=Jason Aalon Butler's new band The Fever have dropped their debut single 'We're Coming In' \u2013 Upset|date=August 14, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Spiritbox<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bringthenoise.com/blog/iwrestledabearonces-courtney-laplante-and-michael|title=Iwrestledabearonce\u2019s&nbsp;Courtney LaPlante and Michael Stringer Reveal New Band Spiritbox, Debut New Single \"The Beauty Of Suffering\" / the NOISE|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Black Sabbath]]\n* Mumakil (Switzerland [[grindcore]]), [[Relapse Records]]\n* Kronos (France [[grindcore]]), [[Deeds of Flesh|Unique Leader Records]]\n* [[The Dillinger Escape Plan]]\n* [[Trap Them]]\n* [[Spawn of Possession]]\n* [[Weekend Nachos]]\n* [[Your Memorial]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://facedownrecords.com/2017/05/10/your-memorial-announce-new-album-final-show/|title=YOUR MEMORIAL ANNOUNCE NEW ALBUM, FINAL SHOW \u2013 Facedown Records|website=facedownrecords.com}}</ref>\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[The Number Twelve Looks Like You]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Aldious]] \u2013 ''Unlimited Diffusion''\n* [[Alestorm]] \u2013 ''[[No Grave But the Sea]]''\n* [[Band-Maid]] \u2013 ''[[Just Bring It (album)|Just Bring It]]''\n* [[DragonForce]] \u2013 ''[[Reaching Into Infinity]]''\n* [[Ensiferum]] \u2013 ''[[Two Paths (album)|Two Paths]]''\n* [[Europe (band)|Europe]]&nbsp;- ''[[Walk the Earth]]''\n* [[Exit Eden]] \u2013 [[Rhapsodies in Black (album)|Rhapsodies in Black]]\n* [[Firewind]] \u2013 ''[[Immortals (album)|Immortals]]''\n* [[Iced Earth]] \u2013 ''[[Incorruptible (album)|Incorruptible]]''\n* [[In This Moment]] \u2013 ''[[Ritual (In This Moment album)|Ritual]]''\n* [[Ithilien (band)|Ithilien]] \u2013 ''Shaping the Soul''\n* [[Kobra and the Lotus]] \u2013 ''[[Prevail I]]''\n* [[Kreator]] \u2013 ''[[Gods of Violence]]''\n* [[L.A. Guns]]&nbsp;- ''[[The Missing Peace (album)|The Missing Peace]]''\n* [[Lovebites (band)|Lovebites]] \u2013 ''[[Awakening from Abyss]]''\n* [[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]] \u2013 ''[[Emperor of Sand]]'' US #7\n* [[Melvins]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[A Walk with Love & Death]]''\n* [[Motionless in White]]&nbsp;- ''[[Graveyard Shift (album)|Graveyard Shift]]''\n* [[Nocturnal Rites]] \u2013 ''[[Phoenix (Nocturnal Rites album)|Phoenix]]''\n* [[Overkill (band)|Overkill]] \u2013 ''[[The Grinding Wheel]]''\n* [[Paradise Lost (band)|Paradise Lost]] \u2013 ''[[Medusa (Paradise Lost album)|Medusa]]''\n* [[Queens of the Stone Age]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Villains (Queens of the Stone Age album)|Villains]]''\n* [[Quiet Riot]] \u2013 ''Road Rage''\n* [[Satyricon (band)|Satyricon]] \u2013 ''[[Deep Calleth Upon Deep]]''\n* [[Seether]] \u2013 ''[[Poison the Parish]]''\n* [[Sepultura]] \u2013 ''[[Machine Messiah (album)|Machine Messiah]]''\n* [[Show-Ya]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Aurora''\n* [[Suffocation (band)|Suffocation]] \u2013 ''[[...Of the Dark Light]]''\n* [[Steel Panther]] \u2013 ''[[Lower the Bar]]''\n* [[Tankard (band)|Tankard]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[One Foot in the Grave (Tankard album)|One Foot in the Grave]]''\n* [[Trivium (band)|Trivium]]&nbsp;- ''[[The Sin and the Sentence]]''\n* [[T.S.O.L.]]&nbsp;- ''The Trigger Complex''\n* [[While She Sleeps]] \u2013 ''[[You Are We]]'' UK #8\n\n===Live albums===\n* [[Babymetal]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live at Tokyo Dome]]''\n\n===Popular songs===\n*[[Alestorm]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Alestorm\"\n*Alestorm&nbsp;\u2013 \"Mexico\"\n*[[DragonForce]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Judgement Day\"\n*DragonForce&nbsp;\u2013 \"Curse of Darkness\"\n*DragonForce&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Ashes of the Dawn]]\"\n*DragonForce&nbsp;\u2013 \"Midnight Madness\"\n*[[Five Finger Death Punch]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Trouble\"\n*Five Finger Death Punch&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Gone Away (song)#Cover versions|Gone Away]]\"\n*[[Foo Fighters]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Run (Foo Fighters song)|Run]]\"\n*[[Iced Earth]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Seven Headed Whore\"\n*Iced Earth&nbsp;\u2013 \"Raven Wing\"\n*Iced Earth&nbsp;\u2013 \"Great Heathen Army\"\n*Iced Earth&nbsp;\u2013 \"Black Flag\"\n*[[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]]&nbsp;- \"[[Steambreather]]\"\n*[[Metallica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Now That We're Dead]]\"\n*[[Stone Sour]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Song 3]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* On January 14, 2017, the [[powerviolence]] band [[Weekend Nachos]] played their final show. Some of the members play in the [[doom metal]] band Ledge.\n* In February, [[Metallica]] performed at the Grammys alongside [[Lady Gaga]].\n* In February, [[AC/DC]] guitarist [[Angus Young]] yet again joined [[Guns N' Roses]] on stage on two of their Australian shows for their [[Not in This Lifetime... Tour]].\n* [[Soundgarden]] and [[Audioslave]] frontman [[Chris Cornell]] dies by suicide on 18 May, aged 52.\n* [[Linkin Park]] vocalist [[Chester Bennington]] dies by suicide on July 20, aged 41.\n* In July, [[Fallujah (band)|Fallujah]] vocalist Alex Hoffman leaves the band.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/fallujah-part-ways-vocalist-alex-hoffman/|title=Fallujah Part Ways With Vocalist Alex Hoffman|website=Loudwire}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/fallujah-parts-ways-with-singer-alex-hofmann/|title=FALLUJAH Parts Ways With Singer ALEX HOFMANN|date=July 14, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalsucks.net/2017/07/14/fallujah-part-ways-with-vocalist-alex-hofmann/|title=Fallujah Part Ways with Vocalist Alex Hofmann \u2013 MetalSucks|date=July 14, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n* In August, [[Code Orange (band)|Code Orange]] performs at the opening of the [[WWE]]'s NXT Takeover Brooklyn show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/code-orange-nxt-takeover-brooklyn/|title=Watch Code Orange Destroy an Arena Crowd at NXT Takeover Brooklyn|website=Loudwire}}</ref>\n*In September, the [[deathcore]] band [[Suicide Silence]] performs the entire album ''[[The Cleansing (album)|The Cleansing]]'' for their tenth anniversary of the release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/suicide-silence-announces-the-cleansing-tenth-anniversary-u-s-tour/|title=SUICIDE SILENCE Announces 'The Cleansing' Tenth-Anniversary U.S. Tour|date=September 6, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n*In September, Michiel Eikenaar, from the [[avant-garde metal]] band Dodecahedron, leaves his position as vocalist. He is replaced by W. Van der Voort, from the [[drone metal]] band Ggu:ll.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalstorm.net/events/news_comments.php?news_id=32322|title=Dodecahedron \u2013 Announce New Vocalist \u2013 Metal Storm|website=www.metalstorm.net}}</ref>\n* [[AC/DC]] founder member and rhythm guitarist [[Malcolm Young]] dies from dementia on 18 November at the age of 64.\n*In December, the [[mathcore]] band [[The Number Twelve Looks Like You]] begins a return performing completely the album ''[[Nuclear. Sad. Nuclear]]'', for their twelve year anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/tour-dates/the-number-twelve-looks-like-you-announces-nuclear-sad-nuclear-anniversary-tour|title=THE NUMBER TWELVE LOOKS LIKE YOU Announces Nuclear. Sad. Nuclear. Anniversary Tour|date=September 29, 2017|publisher=Metal Injection}}</ref>\n* In December 13, [[Nevermore]] and [[Sanctuary (band)|Sanctuary]]'s vocalist, [[Warrel Dane]], passes away at [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/nevermore-and-sanctuary-singer-warrel-dane-dies-of-heart-attack-in-brazil/|title=NEVERMORE And SANCTUARY Singer WARREL DANE Dies Of Heart Attack In Brazil|date=December 13, 2017|publisher=Blabbermouth}}</ref>\n\n==2018==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Iris Official]] (solo band)\n\n===Disbandments===\n*[[Katatonia]]\n*[[Suis La Lune]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[A Perfect Circle]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Eat the Elephant]]''\n* [[Amaranthe]]&nbsp;- ''[[Helix (album)|Helix]]''\n* [[Amorphis]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Queen of Time]]''\n* [[Angelus Apatrida]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Cabaret de la Guillotine''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Pounding the Pavement]]''\n* [[Ashes of Ares]]&nbsp;- ''Well of Souls''\n* [[Bad Wolves]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Disobey]]''\n* [[Band-Maid]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[World Domination (Band-Maid album)|World Domination]]''\n* [[Beyond the Black]]&nbsp;- ''Heart of the Hurricane''\n* [[Black Majesty]]&nbsp;- ''Chil