ster Cult]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Mirrors (Blue \u00d6yster Cult album)|Mirrors]]''\n* [[Foreigner (band)|Foreigner]]&nbsp;- ''[[Head Games (album)|Head Games]]''\n* [[Gamma (band)|Gamma]]&nbsp;- ''[[Gamma 1]]''\n* [[Gillan (band)|Gillan]]&nbsp;- ''[[Mr. Universe (album)|Mr. Universe]]''\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dynasty (Kiss album)|Dynasty]]'' US #9 (Disco single \"I Was Made for Loving You\" led to accusations of sellout, band's popularity suffered for several years)\n* [[Led Zeppelin]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[In Through the Out Door]]'' US #1 UK #1\n* [[Magnum (band)|Magnum]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Magnum II]]''\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Overkill (Mot\u00f6rhead album)|Overkill]]''\n* Mot\u00f6rhead&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bomber (album)|Bomber]]''\n* Mot\u00f6rhead&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[On Parole]]'' (unofficial release from sessions recorded in 1975)\n* [[Nazareth (band)|Nazareth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[No Mean City (album)|No Mean City]]''\n* [[Pat Travers|The Pat Travers Band]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live! Go for What You Know]]''\n* [[Rainbow (English band)|Rainbow]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Down to Earth (Rainbow album)|Down to Earth]]'' UK #6\n* [[Riot (band)|Riot]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Narita (album)|Narita]]''\n* [[Samson (band)|Samson]]&nbsp;- ''[[Survivors (Samson album)|Survivors]]''\n* [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Saxon (album)|Saxon]]''\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Lovedrive]]''\n* [[Slade]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Return to Base]]''\n* [[Ted Nugent]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[State of Shock (Ted Nugent album)|State of Shock]]''\n* [[Thin Lizzy]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Rose: A Rock Legend]]'' UK #2\n* [[Triumph (band)|Triumph]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Just a Game (album)|Just a Game]]''\n* [[Van Halen]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Van Halen II]]'' US #6\n* [[Whitesnake]]&nbsp;- ''[[Lovehunter]]''\n\n===Live albums===\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Unleashed in the East]]'' UK #10, first U.S. success\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Tokyo Tapes (album)|Tokyo Tapes]]'' (USA)\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Strangers in the Night (UFO album)|Strangers in the Night]]'' UK #7\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[AC/DC]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Highway to Hell (song)|Highway to Hell]]\"\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Diamonds & Rust (song)|Diamonds & Rust]]\" (Live)\n* Judas Priest&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Green Manalishi|The Green Manalishi (With the Two-Pronged Crown)]]\" ([[Fleetwood Mac]] [[cover version|cover]])\n* Judas Priest&nbsp;\u2013 \"Hell Bent for Leather\"\n* Judas Priest&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Tyrant (song)|Tyrant]]\" (Live)\n* Judas Priest&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Victim of Changes (song)|Victim of Changes]]\" (Live)\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[I Was Made for Lovin' You]]\"\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Overkill (Mot\u00f6rhead song)|Overkill]]\"\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Another Piece of Meat\"\n* Scorpions&nbsp;\u2013 \"Lovedrive\"\n* [[Van Halen]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Beautiful Girls (Van Halen song)|Beautiful Girls]]\"\n* Van Halen&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Dance the Night Away (Van Halen song)|Dance the Night Away]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* Gary Moore again leaves Thin Lizzy, is eventually replaced by sometime [[Pink Floyd]] guitarist [[Snowy White]]\n* [[Joe Perry (musician)|Joe Perry]] leaves Aerosmith and forms [[The Joe Perry Project]], is replaced in Aerosmith by [[Jimmy Crespo]]. Aerosmith goes into commercial decline.\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]] is kicked out of [[Black Sabbath]] due to problems with drugs and alcohol\n* [[Ronnie James Dio]] becomes the new lead singer of [[Black Sabbath]], is replaced in Rainbow by [[Graham Bonnet]]\n* Michael Schenker departs UFO, replaced by [[Paul Chapman (musician)|Paul Chapman]]\n* ''Sounds'' music paper editor Alan Lewis coins the term \"[[new wave of British heavy metal|New Wave of British Heavy Metal]]\" when looking for a headline to accompany an article [[Geoff Barton]] had written about three young Heavy Metal bands touring together, namely [[Iron Maiden]], [[Samson (band)|Samson]] and [[Angel Witch]].\n\n==1980==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[\u00c1ngeles del Infierno]]\n* [[Bar\u00f3n Rojo]]\n* [[Blitzkrieg (band)|Blitzkrieg]]\n* [[Exodus (American band)|Exodus]]\n* [[King's X]]\n* [[Los Suaves]]\n* [[Manowar]]\n* [[Metal Church]]\n* [[Overkill (band)|Overkill]]\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]]\n* [[Turbo (Polish band)|Turbo]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Led Zeppelin]]\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[Black Sabbath]] ([[Ozzy Osbourne]] and [[Geezer Butler]] replaced by [[Ronnie James Dio]] and [[Geoff Nicholls]]; Nicholls moved to keyboards when Butler rejoined the band)\n* [[Steppenwolf (band)|Steppenwolf]]\n\n===Albums===\nUK Chart information courtesy of the book ''Guinness Hits of the 80s''\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[I'm a Rebel]]''\n* [[AC/DC]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Back in Black]]'' UK #1\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Flush the Fashion]]'' UK #56\n* [[Angel Witch]]&nbsp;- ''[[Angel Witch (album)|Angel Witch]]''\n* [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Tomcattin']]'' US #50\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Heaven and Hell (Black Sabbath album)|Heaven and Hell]]'' UK #9\n* [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Cult\u00f6saurus Erectus]]'' UK #12\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]]&nbsp;- ''Glorious Road''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]]&nbsp;- ''Telephone''\n* [[Budgie (band)]]&nbsp;- ''[[Power Supply (album)|Power Supply]]''\n* [[Cirith Ungol (band)|Cirth Ungol]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Frost and Fire (album)|Frost and Fire]]''\n* [[Def Leppard]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[On Through the Night]]'' UK #15\n* [[Diamond Head (English band)|Diamond Head]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Lightning to the Nations]]''\n* [[Gamma (band)|Gamma]]&nbsp;- ''[[Gamma 2]]''\n* [[Gary Moore]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[G-Force (album)|G-Force]]''\n* [[Gillan (band)|Gillan]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Glory Road (album)|Glory Road]]'' UK #3\n* [[Girl (band)|Girl]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Sheer Greed]]'' UK #33\n* [[Heart (band)|Heart]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Bebe Le Strange]]''\n* [[Girlschool]]&nbsp;\u201