es&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[You Can't Bring Me Down]]\"\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Greenhouse Effect\"\n* Testament&nbsp;\u2013 \"Souls of Black\"\n* Testament&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Legacy\"\n\n===Events===\n* A [[Heavy metal suicide|lawsuit]] alleges that the [[Judas Priest]] song \"[[Better By You, Better Than Me]]\" was the cause of two Nevada teenagers' suicides. Judas Priest win the trial and were acquitted.\n* [[Faith No More]]'s ''[[The Real Thing (Faith No More album)|The Real Thing]]'', carried by the single ''[[Epic (Faith No More song)|Epic]]'', cracks the ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' Top 10.\n* [[Stevie Ray Vaughan]] dies in a helicopter crash on August 27 in Wisconsin.\n* Guitarist [[Adrian Smith]] agrees to leave [[Iron Maiden]] and is replaced by former [[Gillan (band)|Gillan]] and [[White Spirit (band)|White Spirit]] guitarist [[Janick Gers]].\n* The heavy metal music festival [[Wacken Open Air]] is first performed with bands of German origin like Motoslug and [[Wizzard]].\n* [[Monsters of Rock|Monsters Of Rock Festival]] returns after taking a break in 1989, due to the 2 deaths, that occurred during [[Guns n' Roses]] set in 1988.  Features Headliner [[Whitesnake]], plus support from [[Aerosmith]], [[Poison (American band)|Poison]], [[Quireboys]] and [[Thunder (band)|Thunder]].\n\n==1991==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Angra_(band)|Angra]]\n* [[Behemoth (band)|Behemoth]]\n* [[Belphegor (band)|Belphegor]]\n* [[Burzum]]\n* [[Cradle of Filth]]\n* [[Crematory (band)|Crematory]]\n* [[Crowbar (American band)|Crowbar]]\n* [[Down (band)|Down]]\n* [[Emperor (band)|Emperor]]\n* [[Enslaved (band)|Enslaved]]\n* [[Hank Williams III]]\n* [[Illdisposed]]\n* [[Kamelot]]\n* [[Machine Head (band)|Machine Head]]\n* [[Nevermore]]\n* [[Oasis (band)|Oasis]]\n* [[Rage Against the Machine]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Death Angel]]\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]] (Fourth hiatus)\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* Vanilla Fudge\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[