]]\"\n* M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Primal Scream (song)|Primal Scream]]\"\n* [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Smells Like Teen Spirit]]\"\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[No More Tears (Ozzy Osbourne song)|No More Tears]]\"\n* Ozzy Osbourne&nbsp;\u2013 \"Time After Time\"\n* Ozzy Osbourne&nbsp;\u2013 \"Road To Nowhere\"\n* [[Pearl Jam]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Alive\"\n* [[Savatage]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Jesus Saves\"\n* [[Skid Row (American band)|Skid Row]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[In a Darkened Room]]\"\n* Skid Row&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Monkey Business (Skid Row song)|Monkey Business]]\"\n* Skid Row&nbsp;\u2013 \"Quicksand Jesus\"\n* Skid Row&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Slave to the Grind (song)|Slave to the Grind]]\"\n* Skid Row&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Wasted Time (Skid Row song)|Wasted Time]]\"\n* [[Sodom (band)|Sodom]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Saw Is the Law]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]]'s collaboration with [[Chuck D]] for a recording of \"[[Bring The Noise]]\" and subsequent joint tour with [[Public Enemy (band)|Public Enemy]] launch [[rap metal]].\n\n* [[Metallica]]'s self-titled ''[[Metallica (album)|Black Album]]'' becomes the first [[thrash metal]] album to hit No.1 in the Billboard music charts, after they streamlined their sound and hired [[Bob Rock]] to produce their album.\n* Queen singer [[Freddie Mercury]] dies of [[AIDS]] induced [[bronchial pneumonia]].\n* [[Skid Row (American band)|Skid Row]], [[Guns N' Roses]], and [[Metallica]]'s albums all debut #1, at that time they were all in tour together.\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] Drummer&nbsp;\u2013 [[Eric Carr]] dies on November 24, 1991, Eric Carr died at the age of 41 of complications from cancer. As a tribute, the group's 1992 release Revenge featured what is said to be the only drum solo Carr ever recorded with the band, which was titled \"Carr Jam 1981\".\n* [[AC/DC]] headlines the [[Monsters of Rock]] festival at Donington, England on a bill which includes [[Metallica]], [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]], [[Queensr\u00ffche]] and [[The Black Crowes]].\n* [[Steve Clark]], the co-lead guitarist of [[Def Leppard]], died at the age of 30 on January 8, 1991 from an overdose of drugs and alcohol.\n* Izzy Stradlin leaves Guns N' Roses.\n\n==1992==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Alarum (band)|Alarum]]\n* [[Amon Amarth]]\n* [[Bush (British band)|Bush]]\n* [[Edguy]]\n* [[Esoteric (band)|Esoteric]]\n* Groundswell/[[Three Days Grace]]\n* [[Moonspell]]\n* [[Vision of Disorder]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Alice in Chains]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dirt (Alice in Chains album)|Dirt]]'' US #6\n* Alice in Chains&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Sap (album)|Sap]]'' (EP)\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Worth the Weight]]''\n* [[At the Gates]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Red in the Sky Is Ours]]''\n* [[Axel Rudi Pell]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Eternal Prisoner]]''\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dehumaniser]]''\n* [[Blind Guardian]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Somewhere Far Beyond]]''\n* [[Body Count (band)|Body Count]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Body Count (album)|Body Count]]''\n* [[Bolt Thrower (band)|Bolt Thrower]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The IVth Crusade]]''\n* [[Bon Jovi]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Keep the Faith]]'' US #5 UK #1\n* [[Cannibal Corpse]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Tomb of the Mutilated]]''\n* [[Darkthrone]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[A Blaze in the Northern Sky]]''\n* [[Def Leppard]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Adrenalize]]'' US #1 UK #1\n* [[Dream Theater]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Images and Words]]''\n* [[Exciter (band)|Exciter]]&nbsp;- ''[[Kill After Kill]]''\n* [[Exodus (band)|Exodus]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Force of Habit]]''\n* [[Faith No More]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Angel Dust (Faith No More album)|Angel Dust]]'' US #10 UK #2\n* [[Fear Factory]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Soul of a New Machine]]''\n* [[Flotsam and Jetsam (band)|Flotsam and Jetsam]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Cuatro (Flotsam and Jetsam album)|Cuatro]]''\n* [[Gary Moore]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[After Hours (Gary Moore album)|After Hours]]''\n* [[Girlschool]]&nbsp;- ''[[Girlschool (album)|Girlschool]]''\n* [[Iced Earth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Night of the Stormr