en Flow]]\" US #3\n* [[Pearl Jam]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Jeremy (song)|Jeremy]]\" US #5\n* [[Rage Against the Machine]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Killing in the Name]]\"\n* [[Suicidal Tendencies]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Asleep at the Wheel\"\n* Suicidal Tendencies&nbsp;\u2013 \"I'll Hate You Better\"\n* Suicidal Tendencies&nbsp;\u2013 \"Monopoly on Sorrow\"\n* Suicidal Tendencies&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Nobody Hears]]\"\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Electric Crown\"\n* Testament&nbsp;\u2013 \"Return to Serenity\"\n\n===Events===\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]'s drummer Phil Taylor finally leaves after recording \"Ain't No Nice Guy\" for the ''[[March \u00f6r Die]]'' album. The drummer on that album is Tommy Aldridge, who was replaced by Mikkey Dee after recording the album.\n* In April, [[The Freddie Mercury Tribute Concert]] is held. Top heavy metal acts such as [[Metallica]], [[Guns N' Roses]], [[Def Leppard]], [[Extreme (band)|Extreme]] and the heavy metal parody band [[Spinal Tap (band)|Spinal Tap]] perform, as well as heavy metal/hard rock legends such as [[Robert Plant]] ([[Led Zeppelin]]), [[Tony Iommi]] ([[Black Sabbath]]) and [[Roger Daltrey]] ([[The Who]]).\n* [[Iron Maiden]] headlines the [[Monsters of Rock]] festival at Donington, England on a bill which includes [[Skid Row (American band)|Skid Row]], [[Thunder (band)|Thunder]], [[Slayer]], [[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]] and [[The Almighty (band)|The Almighty]].\n\n==1993==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Apocalyptica]]\n* [[Children of Bodom]]\n* [[Coal Chamber]]\n* [[Dark Funeral]]\n* [[Dimmu Borgir]]\n* [[Fight (band)|Fight]]\n* [[Fury (Australian band)|Fury]]\n* [[HammerFall]]\n* [[Korn]]\n* [[Korpiklaani]]\n* [[Mournful Congregation]]\n* [[Mushroomhead]]\n* [[Nile (band)|Nile]]\n* [[Rhapsody of Fire]]\n* [[Sacrificium]]\n* [[Theatre of Tragedy]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Judas Priest]] (Hiatus)\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Objection Overruled (album)