e set to fly out on a promotional tour in the [[United States]]. Edwards' car was subsequently found near the [[Severn Bridge]], a popular suicide spot between [[England]] and [[Wales]] however, his body has never been found.\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]'s guitarist Michael \"[[W\u00fcrzel]]\" Burston leaves the band.\n* MTV abruptly canceled the music television program [[Headbangers Ball|Headbanger's Ball]] in January 1995.\n* After a series of private tragedies, drummer [[Ingo Schwichtenberg]] felt unable to cope with life and committed suicide, to honor his memory, guitarist [[Roland Grapow]] bought his [[Drum kit]].\n* Los Angeles-based heavy metal radio station [[KNAC]] goes off the air and is replaced by [[KBUE]].\n\n==1996==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[3 Doors Down]]\n* [[Arch Enemy]]\n* [[Control Denied]]\n* [[Danko Jones]]\n* [[Decapitated (band)|Decapitated]]\n* [[God Forbid]]\n* [[Gojira (band)|Gojira]]\n* [[Letzte Instanz]]\n* [[Linkin Park]]\n* [[Lordi]]\n* [[Mudvayne]]\n* [[Nightwish]]\n* [[Norther]]\n* [[Pain (musical project)|Pain]]\n* [[Queens of the Stone Age]]\n* [[Saurom]]\n* [[Segression]]\n* [[Shadows Fall]]\n* [[SHOCKLET]]\n* [[Skillet (band)|Skillet]]\n* [[Slapshock]]\n* [[Spineshank]]\n* [[Tristania (band)|Tristania]]\n* [[Within Temptation]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Down (band)|Down]]\n* [[Skid Row (American band)|Skid Row]]\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[Judas Priest]](Back from hiatus with new singer [[Tim \"Ripper\" Owens]])\n* [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] (back in full makeup and costume with [[Ace Frehley]] and [[Peter Criss]])\n\n===Albums===\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Predator (album)|Predator]]''\n* [[Alice in Chains]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Unplugged (Alice in Chains)|Unplugged]]'' US #6\n* [[Holy_Land_(album)|Angra - Holy Land]]\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Plugged in Permanent]]''\n* [[Apocalyptica]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Plays Metallica by Four Cellos]]''\n* [[Arch Enemy (band)|Arch Enemy]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Earth (Arc