nderstone (band)|Thunderstone]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Tool of the Devil\"\n* [[Within Temptation]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Angels (Within Temptation song)|Angels]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* [[Tarja Turunen]] is dismissed from [[Nightwish]] via an open letter after a concert in the Hartwall Areena (Helsinki) on October 21.\n* [[Static-X]] lead guitarist [[Tripp Eisen]] was arrested in February for \"lewd conduct against children.\"\n* Korn guitarist Brian \"Head\" Welch leaves the band after becoming a born again Christian and having conflicts with the band's subject matter.\n* Former [[Vader (band)|Vader]] drummer Docent dies.\n* [[System of a Down]] is the first band since the Beatles to have two albums debut at #1 in the same year.\n* After Grammy Awards, #1 hits, and 3 out of 5 albums debuting at #1, [[System of a Down]] goes on an indefinite hiatus.\n\n==2006==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Asking Alexandria]]\n* [[Black Veil Brides]]\n* [[Daron Malakian and Scars on Broadway]]\n* [[Dethklok]]\n* [[Hellyeah]]\n* [[In Hearts Wake]]\n* [[Mammal (band)|Mammal]]\n* [[Thy Art Is Murder]]\n* [[The Virginmarys]]\n* [[Whitechapel (band)|Whitechapel]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[The 22-20s]]\n* [[Fear Factory]]\n* [[Limp Bizkit]] (until 2009)\n\n===Albums===\n* [[After the Burial]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Forging a Future Self]]\n* [[Agalloch]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Ashes Against the Grain]]''\n* [[Amon Amarth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[With Oden on Our Side]]''\n* [[Amorphis]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Eclipse (Amorphis album)|Eclipse]]''\n* [[Aurora_Consurgens_(album)|Angra - Aurora Consurgens]]\n* [[April Wine]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Roughly Speaking]]''\n* [[Architects (British band)|Architects]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Nightmares (Architects album)|Nightmares]]''\n* [[Atreyu (band)|Atreyu]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[A Death-Grip on Yesterday]]'' US #9\n* [[Audioslave]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Revelations (Audioslave album)|Revelations]]'' US #2\n* [[Axel Rudi Pell]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Mystica (Axel Rudi Pell album)|Mystica]]''\n* [[Benighted]]&nbsp;\u2013