ally recorded during the New Years weekend of 1981\u201382\n* [[Heart (band)|Heart]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dreamboat Annie Live]]''\n* [[Manowar]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Gods of War Live]]''\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[That One Night: Live in Buenos Aires]]''\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Better Mot\u00f6rhead than Dead: Live at Hammersmith]]''\n* [[Opeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Roundhouse Tapes]]''\n* [[Queensr\u00ffche]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Mindcrime at the Moore]]''\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Live Throughout the Years''\n* [[Vanilla Fudge]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Good Good Rockin'&nbsp;\u2013 Live at Rockpalast''\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[As I Lay Dying (band)|As I Lay Dying]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Nothing Left (As I Lay Dying song)|Nothing Left]]\"\n* [[Avenged Sevenfold]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Afterlife (Avenged Sevenfold song)|Afterlife]]\"\n* Avenged Sevenfold&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Almost Easy]]\"\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Ear In The Wall\"\n* Black Sabbath&nbsp;\u2013 \"Shadow Of The Wind\"\n* Black Sabbath&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Devil Cried\"\n* [[Chevelle (band)|Chevelle]]&nbsp;- \"[[I Get It]]\"\n* [[Cog (band)|Cog]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"What If\"\n* [[DevilDriver]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Clouds Over California\"\n* [[Dream Theater]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Constant Motion]]\"\n* [[Epica (band)|Epica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Never Enough (Epica song)|Never Enough]]\"\n* [[Exodus (American band)|Exodus]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Funeral Hymn\"\n* Exodus&nbsp;\u2013 \"Riot Act\"\n* [[Korn]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Evolution (Korn song)|Evolution]]\"\n* [[Linkin Park]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Given Up]]\"\n* [[Machine Head (band)|Machine Head]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Halo (Machine Head song)|Halo]]\"\n* Machine Head&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Aesthetics of Hate]]\"\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[\u00c0 Tout le Monde#2007 version|\u00c0 Tout le Monde (Set Me Free)]]\"\n* Megadeth&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Never Walk Alone... A Call to Arms]]\"\n* Megadeth&nbsp;\u2013 \"Washington is Next!\"\n* [[Nightwish]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Amaranth (song)|Amaranth]]\"\n* [[Sonata Arctica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Paid in Full (Sonata Arctica song)|Paid in Full]]\"\n* [[Tarja Turunen]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[I Walk Alone (Tarja song)|I Walk Alone]]\"\n* [[Thunderstone (band)|Thunderstone]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Face in the Mirror\"\n* [[Type O Negative]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Profit of Doom]]\"\n* [[Within Temptation]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[What Have You Done]]\"\n* Within Temptation&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Howling (EP)|The Howling]]\"\n\n===Events===\n* Wayne Knupp, original vocalist for [[Devourment]] died on September 15.\n* Pat Mason of [[Arsonists Get All The Girls]] died on the morning of November 30, his 21st birthday.\n* [[Extreme (band)|Extreme]] reunite for the third time, announcing plans for a world tour next year, as well as a new studio album, which will be their first since 1995's ''[[Waiting for the Punchline]]''.\n* [[Led Zeppelin]] get back together one more time for one concert in London.\n* [[In Sorte Diaboli]] ([[Dimmu Borgir]]) becomes the first extreme metal album ever to hit the #1 in a [[Record chart]], achieving that position in Norway.\n* Andreas Sydow leaves [[Darkane]], being replaced by Jens Broman.\n* [[Witold Kieltyka]], drummer for [[Decapitated (band)|Decapitated]], is killed in a car crash in October.\n* Vocalist, Damo and manager, Andy of [[The Red Shore]], died in December.\n* [[Anette Olzon]] joins [[Nightwish]] as their new lead vocalist.\n* [[Peter Lindgren (musician)|Peter Lindgren]] leaves [[Opeth]].\n* [[Jani Liimatainen]] is fired from [[Sonata Arctica]] and replaced by [[Elias Viljanen]].\n* Jacob Bredahl leaves [[Hatesphere]].\n* [[Mark St. John]], guitarist of [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] in 1984, dies in April.\n* The song Final Six from [[Slayer]] won in the [[Best Metal Performance]] category at the [[50th Grammy Awards]].\n* [[Meiju Enho]] leaves [[Ensiferum]].\n* [[Paul Raven (musician)|Paul Raven]], bassist for Ministry and former [[Killing Joke]] bassist, dies in October.\n* [[Kevin DuBrow]], lead singer for [[Quiet Riot]], dies in November.\n* [[Matt Barlow]] returns as lead singer of [[Iced Earth]].\n* [[Ramallah]] disbands.\n* Matte Modin is fired from [[Dark Funeral]], for disrupting their live performance schedule through deceit, according to the band. He is replaced by Nils Fj\u00e4llstr\u00f6m of [[Aeon (band)|Aeon]], who is given the stage name \"Dominator\".\n* [[Gaahl]] and [[King ov Hell]] part ways from [[Gorgoroth]] founding member [[Infernus]] with the intention of using the band's name and assets themselves, igniting the [[Gorgoroth name dispute]].\n\n==2008==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Aldious]]\n* Avalanche/[[Amaranthe]]\n* [[Battle Beast (band)|Battle Beast]]\n* [[Chickenfoot]]\n* [[Empires of Eden]]\n* [[Exhorder]]\n* [[Falling in Reverse]]\n* [[Ghost (Swedish band)|Ghost]]\n* [[Twelve Foot Ninja]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n* [[Alabama Thunderpussy]]\n* [[Beneath the Sky]]\n* [[Byzantine (band)|Byzantine]]\n* [[Celtic Frost]]\n* [[Dead to Fall]]\n* [[Demigod (band)|Demigod]]\n* [[The Duskfall]]\n* [[From Autumn To Ashes]]\n* [[Himsa]]\n* [[Knorkator]]\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]\n* [[Ministry (band)|Ministry]]\n* [[Sieges Even]]\n* [[SikTh]]\n* [[Spineshank]] in February\n* [[Still Remains]]\n* [[The Red Death]]\n* [[The Agony Scene]]\n* [[Remove the Veil]]\n* Whispering Gallery\n\n===Reformed bands===\n* [[At the Gates]] (for a few shows)\n* [[Carcass (band)|Carcass]] (for touring)\n* [[Einherjer]] (for touring)\n* [[Forbidden (band)|Forbidden]] (for a few shows)\n* [[Krokus (band)|Krokus]]\n* [[Liquid Tension Experiment]] (for touring)\n* [[Living Sacrifice]]\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]\n* [[Spineshank]] in August\n* [[Vision of Disorder]]\n\n===Albums===\n* [[AC/DC]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Black Ice (album)|Black Ice]]'' US #1 UK #1 AUS #1\n* [[After the Burial]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Rareform]]\n* [[Alice Cooper]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Along Came a Spider (album)|Along Came a Spider]]''\n* [[Amon Amarth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Twilight of the Thunder God]]''\n* [[Avantasia]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Scarecrow (