013 ''[[House of Gold & Bones \u2013 Part 2]]''\n* [[Stratovarius]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Nemesis (Stratovarius album)|Nemesis]]''\n* [[Suicidal Tendencies]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[13 (Suicidal Tendencies album)|13]]''\n* [[Tesseract (band)|Tesseract]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Altered State (Tesseract album)|Altered State]]''\n* [[Trivium (band)|Trivium]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Vengeance Falls]]''<ref>[[Vengeance Falls]]</ref>\n* [[Turbo (Polish band)|Turbo]]&nbsp;- ''Pi\u0105ty \u017cywio\u0142''\n* [[Turisas]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Turisas2013]]''\n* [[T\u00fdr (band)|T\u00fdr]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Valkyrja (album)|Valkyrja]]''\n* [[Vicious Rumors]]&nbsp;- ''[[Electric Punishment (Vicious Rumors album)|Electric Punishment]]''\n* [[Volbeat (band)|Volbeat]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Outlaw Gentlemen & Shady Ladies]]'' US #9 CAN #1 DEN #1\n* [[We Came as Romans]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Tracing Back Roots]]'' US #8\n\n===Live albums===\n* [[Babymetal]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live: Legend I, D, Z Apocalypse]]''\n* [[Black Label Society]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Unblackened]]''\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live... Gathered in Their Masses]]''\n* [[Deep Purple]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Now What?!#The Now What?! Live Tapes bonus CD|The Now What?! Live Tapes]]''\n* [[Dream Theater]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live at Luna Park]]''\n* [[Iced Earth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Live in Ancient Kourion]]''\n* [[Judas Priest]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Epitaph''\n* [[Kreator]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Dying Alive''\n* [[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Live At Brixton''\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Countdown to Extinction: Live]]''\n* [[Rainbow (English band)|Rainbow]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Black Masquerade''\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Clockwork Angels Tour]]''\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''MTV Unplugged \u2013 Live in Athens''\n* [[Testament (band)|Testament]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Dark Roots of Thrash]]''\n\n===Extended plays===\n* [[Halestorm]]&nbsp;- ''[[Reanimate 2.0: The Covers EP]]''\n* [[Stone Temple Pilots]]&nbsp;- ''[[High Rise (EP)|High Rise]]''\n\n===Popular songs===\n* [[After the Burial]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"A Wolf Amongst Ravens\"\n* [[Amaranthe]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"The Nexus\"\n* Amaranthe&nbsp;\u2013 \"Burn with Me\"\n* [[Avenged Sevenfold]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Hail to the King (song)|Hail to the King]]\"\n* [[Black Sabbath]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[End of the Beginning (song)|End of the Beginning]]\"\n* Black Sabbath&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[God Is Dead?]]\"\n* Black Sabbath&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Loner (Black Sabbath song)|Loner]]\"\n* [[Black Veil Brides]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"In The End\"\n* [[Bullet for My Valentine]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Riot\"\n* [[Device (heavy metal band)|Device]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Vilify (song)|Vilify]]\"\n* [[Dream Theater]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[The Enemy Inside (Dream Theater song)|The Enemy Inside]]\"\n* [[Falling In Reverse]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Alone (Falling in Reverse song)|Alone]]\"\n* Falling In Reverse&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Fashionably Late (Falling in Reverse song)|Fashionably Late]]\"\n* [[Five Finger Death Punch]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Battle Born (song)|Battle Born]]\"\n* Five Finger Death Punch&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Lift Me Up (Five Finger Death Punch song)|Lift Me Up]]\" (featuring [[Rob Halford]])\n* [[Ghost (Swedish band)|Ghost]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Secular Haze\"\n* Ghost&nbsp;\u2013 \"Year Zero\"\n* [[Helloween]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Burning Sun\"\n* Helloween&nbsp;\u2013 \"Hold Me in Your Arms\"\n* Helloween&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Nabatea (song)|Nabatea]]\"\n* Helloween&nbsp;\u2013 \"Waiting for the Thunder\"\n* [[Killswitch Engage]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"In Due Time\"\n* [[Korn]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Love & Meth\"\n* Korn&nbsp;\u2013 \"Never Never\"\n* Korn&nbsp;\u2013 \"Spike In My Veins\"\n* [[Megadeth]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Super Collider (song)|Super Collider]]\"\n* [[Powerwolf]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Sacred & Wild\"\n* Powerwolf&nbsp;\u2013 \"In the Name of God\"\n* [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Night of the Wolf\"\n* Saxon&nbsp;\u2013 \"Warriors of the Road\"\n* [[Sevendust]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Decay\"\n* [[Sonata Arctica]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Alone In Heaven\"\n* [[Stratovarius]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Unbreakable\"\n* Stratovarius&nbsp;\u2013 \"Halcyon Days\"\n* [[Tesseract (band)|Tesseract]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Of Mind: Nocturne\"\n* [[Trivium (band)|Trivium]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Brave This Storm\"\n* Trivium&nbsp;\u2013 \"Strife\"\n* [[Turisas]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"For Your Own Good\"\n* [[Turisas]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Ten More Miles\"\n* [[Volbeat (band)|Volbeat]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"Room 24\" (featuring King Diamond)\n* [[Within Temptation]]&nbsp;\u2013 \"[[Paradise (What About Us?)]]\" (featuring [[Tarja Turunen]])\n\n===Events===\n* After his car crash in 2008, original [[Deftones]] bassist [[Chi Cheng (musician)|Chi Cheng]] went into a [[coma]]. In April 2013 he died in hospital.\n* As part of the 2013 legs of their [[Maiden England World Tour]], [[Iron Maiden]] will perform at their record breaking fifth [[Download Festival]], their third performance at the [[Rock in Rio]] festival, as well as their very first show in [[Paraguay]].\n* On May 6 [[Iced Earth]] drummer Brent Smedley steps down from the band due to personal reasons, was replaced by drummer Raphael Saini to play on the recording of their eleventh studio album which would later be confirmed titled as ''[[Plagues of Babylon]]'' as well as filling in on tour, [[Jon Dette]] took over as the touring drummer in November that year.\n* [[Black Sabbath]]'s new album ''[[13 (Black Sabbath album)|13]]'' became the first and only album by Black Sabbath to reach number 1 in America after 45 years of recording. Originally the closest they ever got to the number 1 spot in America was with their album ''[[Master of Reality]]'' which peaked at number 3.\n* Due to legal reasons, [[Ghost (Swedish band)|Ghost]] in the United States was forced to change their name to Ghost B.C.\n* Due to [[Tony Campos]] owning 50% name rights to the band, [[Wayne Static]] was forced to split up [[Static X]] again.\n* Former Iron Maiden drummer [[Clive Burr]] died at his home in London due to complications of [[multiple sclerosis]].\n* [[Iron Maiden]] re-released their 1989 live concert VHS/live album ''[[Maiden England]]'' under the new title ''Maiden England '88'' on DVD, CD, and LP formats.\n* [[Lamb of God (band)|Lamb of God]] singer [[Randy Blythe]] was acquitted of his manslaughter charges and was released.\n* [[Lostprophets]] frontman [[Ian Watkins (Lostprophets)|Ian Watkins]] pleaded guilty to a series of child sex offences including the attempted rape of a baby and was sentenced to 35 years in prison. A month prior to his guilty plea, the remaining members of Lostprophets announced that they were disbanding.\n* [[Rob Caggiano]] departed from [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]] to pursue a different musical direction. A couple of weeks later, it was announced that he had joined [[Volbeat]] whom he recently helped with production on their most recent album.\n* [[Slayer]] drummer [[Dave Lombardo]] was dismissed from the band prior to the [[Soundwave (Australian music festival)|Australian Soundwave Festival]] and was temporarily replaced by former drummer [[Jon Dette]]. Former drummer [[Paul Bostaph]] later returned to fill-in on drums full-time.\n* [[Slayer]] guitarist and songwriter [[Jeff Hanneman]] died of liver failure on May 2, 2013, in a local Los Angeles hospital near his home in Southern California's Inland Empire. On May 9, 2013, the official cause of death was announced as alcohol-related cirrhosis.\n* Hammer Studios in Hamburg, Germany burned down on 18 November. No-one was hurt but a lot of valuable equipment was destroyed. [[Gamma Ray (band)|Gamma Ray]]'s upcoming album along with [[Deep Purple]]'s new live album are expected to be delayed.\n* [[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]] On December 12, 2013, the band announced through their official website that long-time member and drummer, Joey Jordison had parted ways with the band after 18 years citing personal reasons.\n\n==2014==\n\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Act of Defiance]]\n* [[Wovenwar]]\n\n===Disbandments===\n*[[Chimaira]]\n*[[Newsted]]\n\n===