rooklyn/|title=Watch Code Orange Destroy an Arena Crowd at NXT Takeover Brooklyn|website=Loudwire}}</ref>\n*In September, the [[deathcore]] band [[Suicide Silence]] performs the entire album ''[[The Cleansing (album)|The Cleansing]]'' for their tenth anniversary of the release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/suicide-silence-announces-the-cleansing-tenth-anniversary-u-s-tour/|title=SUICIDE SILENCE Announces 'The Cleansing' Tenth-Anniversary U.S. Tour|date=September 6, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n*In September, Michiel Eikenaar, from the [[avant-garde metal]] band Dodecahedron, leaves his position as vocalist. He is replaced by W. Van der Voort, from the [[drone metal]] band Ggu:ll.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalstorm.net/events/news_comments.php?news_id=32322|title=Dodecahedron \u2013 Announce New Vocalist \u2013 Metal Storm|website=www.metalstorm.net}}</ref>\n* [[AC/DC]] founder member and rhythm guitarist [[Malcolm Young]] dies from dementia on 18 November at the age of 64.\n*In December, the [[mathcore]] band [[The Number Twelve Looks Like You]] begins a return performing completely the album ''[[Nuclear. Sad. Nuclear]]'', for their twelve year anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/tour-dates/the-number-twelve-looks-like-you-announces-nuclear-sad-nuclear-anniversary-tour|title=THE NUMBER TWELVE LOOKS LIKE YOU Announces Nuclear. Sad. Nuclear. Anniversary Tour|date=September 29, 2017|publisher=Metal Injection}}</ref>\n* In December 13, [[Nevermore]] and [[Sanctuary (band)|Sanctuary]]'s vocalist, [[Warrel Dane]], passes away at [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/nevermore-and-sanctuary-singer-warrel-dane-dies-of-heart-attack-in-brazil/|title=NEVERMORE And SANCTUARY Singer WARREL DANE Dies Of Heart Attack In Brazil|date=December 13, 2017|publisher=Blabbermouth}}</ref>\n\n==2018==\n===Newly formed bands===\n* [[Iris Official]] (solo band)\n\n===Disbandments===\n*[[Katatonia]